WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.491 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:01.491 --> 00:00:10.450 align:middle line:90%


00:00:10.450 --> 00:00:13.320 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA GARR: Hi, I'm Lisa Garr,
host of "Gaiam Inspirations."

00:00:13.320 --> 00:00:15.600 align:middle line:84%
So how good are you
at surrendering?

00:00:15.600 --> 00:00:17.150 align:middle line:90%
Let me ask you a few questions.

00:00:17.150 --> 00:00:21.450 align:middle line:84%
Do you recognize that you
cannot control everything?

00:00:21.450 --> 00:00:25.730 align:middle line:84%
Can you admit that you don't
always have to be right?

00:00:25.730 --> 00:00:27.530 align:middle line:90%
Can you be spontaneous?

00:00:27.530 --> 00:00:30.500 align:middle line:84%
Can you enjoy life
and stop long enough

00:00:30.500 --> 00:00:33.170 align:middle line:90%
to let a beautiful day in?

00:00:33.170 --> 00:00:34.950 align:middle line:90%
Joining me is Dr. Judith Orloff.

00:00:34.950 --> 00:00:38.160 align:middle line:84%
She's a psychiatrist
and an intuition expert.

00:00:38.160 --> 00:00:40.510 align:middle line:84%
She's the author of her
newly released book called

00:00:40.510 --> 00:00:45.140 align:middle line:84%
"The Ecstasy of Surrender:
12 Surprising Ways

00:00:45.140 --> 00:00:47.540 align:middle line:84%
Letting Go Can
Empower Your Life."

00:00:47.540 --> 00:00:48.250 align:middle line:90%
Welcome.

00:00:48.250 --> 00:00:49.490 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for being here.

00:00:49.490 --> 00:00:51.156 align:middle line:84%
>>DR. JUDITH ORLOFF:
Oh, you're welcome.

00:00:51.156 --> 00:00:54.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I joke because the
therapy session begins now.

00:00:54.100 --> 00:00:56.164 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: The surrender
therapy session.

00:00:56.164 --> 00:00:57.274 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, please.

00:00:57.274 --> 00:00:59.440 align:middle line:84%
This show is for me today
and for everyone listening

00:00:59.440 --> 00:01:03.400 align:middle line:84%
because how many people have
you encountered since coming out

00:01:03.400 --> 00:01:06.166 align:middle line:84%
with the book that
have control issues?

00:01:06.166 --> 00:01:07.120 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Hahaha.

00:01:07.120 --> 00:01:07.750 align:middle line:90%
Everybody.

00:01:07.750 --> 00:01:09.415 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Everybody, right?

00:01:09.415 --> 00:01:09.956 align:middle line:90%
What is that?

00:01:09.956 --> 00:01:11.950 align:middle line:90%
What does it stem from, Judith?

00:01:11.950 --> 00:01:15.380 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Well, I think our
society is so control oriented

00:01:15.380 --> 00:01:18.620 align:middle line:84%
that we're not taught as
children to surrender.

00:01:18.620 --> 00:01:21.510 align:middle line:84%
You know, the assets
of really letting go

00:01:21.510 --> 00:01:23.380 align:middle line:90%
and not clenching and forcing.

00:01:23.380 --> 00:01:26.550 align:middle line:84%
We're taught to push the river,
make our dreams come true,

00:01:26.550 --> 00:01:28.170 align:middle line:84%
and make that
relationship happen,

00:01:28.170 --> 00:01:30.880 align:middle line:84%
and make that job happen,
and do it all on will.

00:01:30.880 --> 00:01:33.590 align:middle line:84%
And what I'm saying
is that surrender

00:01:33.590 --> 00:01:37.310 align:middle line:84%
is knowing when to do that,
when to really go forward,

00:01:37.310 --> 00:01:41.410 align:middle line:84%
and when to let go and let
spirit come in to help you.

00:01:41.410 --> 00:01:42.990 align:middle line:90%
Because we're in a flow.

00:01:42.990 --> 00:01:45.410 align:middle line:84%
And if you're just doing
everything on self will,

00:01:45.410 --> 00:01:47.540 align:middle line:84%
you're going to get
tired very quickly.

00:01:47.540 --> 00:01:50.220 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, I know this.

00:01:50.220 --> 00:01:54.180 align:middle line:84%
So why is it so hard, though,
for people to surrender?

00:01:54.180 --> 00:01:55.360 align:middle line:90%
Why is that so challenging?

00:01:55.360 --> 00:01:57.151 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Well, I think
in the West, people

00:01:57.151 --> 00:02:01.430 align:middle line:84%
associate surrender with defeat,
with weakness, with giving up.

00:02:01.430 --> 00:02:05.020 align:middle line:84%
They look at it in a military
way, like you're giving up.

00:02:05.020 --> 00:02:07.810 align:middle line:84%
And that's so not what
I'm talking about.

00:02:07.810 --> 00:02:11.530 align:middle line:84%
Surrender as a devotional path
in many spiritual practices

00:02:11.530 --> 00:02:13.560 align:middle line:90%
is common throughout the world.

00:02:13.560 --> 00:02:16.090 align:middle line:84%
It's just not in
Western culture.

00:02:16.090 --> 00:02:17.950 align:middle line:84%
So as I've been
touring with the book,

00:02:17.950 --> 00:02:20.370 align:middle line:84%
and I've been in particularly
mainstream media,

00:02:20.370 --> 00:02:24.060 align:middle line:84%
I really have to educate people
about what surrender means

00:02:24.060 --> 00:02:26.290 align:middle line:84%
because it's very
scary to people

00:02:26.290 --> 00:02:28.500 align:middle line:84%
not to be in control
every minute.

00:02:28.500 --> 00:02:30.900 align:middle line:84%
But the good news
and the bad news

00:02:30.900 --> 00:02:33.370 align:middle line:84%
is you can't be in control
every minute no matter what.

00:02:33.370 --> 00:02:35.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, I mean,
let's talk about why

00:02:35.120 --> 00:02:36.830 align:middle line:84%
we want to control
in the first place.

00:02:36.830 --> 00:02:38.140 align:middle line:90%
Is it for safety?

00:02:38.140 --> 00:02:40.450 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Yeah, it's to
feel safe, to feel secure.

00:02:40.450 --> 00:02:42.090 align:middle line:90%
I can control my environment.

00:02:42.090 --> 00:02:46.880 align:middle line:84%
I can control this life, which
we really can't because we

00:02:46.880 --> 00:02:47.560 align:middle line:90%
begin here.

00:02:47.560 --> 00:02:48.680 align:middle line:90%
We live our lives.

00:02:48.680 --> 00:02:51.480 align:middle line:84%
And then the ultimate surrender,
which is the last chapter,

00:02:51.480 --> 00:02:53.800 align:middle line:84%
is letting go to death
and the afterlife.

00:02:53.800 --> 00:02:57.160 align:middle line:84%
There comes a time where
we all must surrender.

00:02:57.160 --> 00:02:59.095 align:middle line:90%
It's so inevitable in our cells.

00:02:59.095 --> 00:03:01.470 align:middle line:90%
It's something that's for sure.

00:03:01.470 --> 00:03:03.180 align:middle line:90%
And we can't fight it.

00:03:03.180 --> 00:03:04.840 align:middle line:90%
And this terrifies people.

00:03:04.840 --> 00:03:08.910 align:middle line:84%
The smaller surrenders sometimes
mimic the larger surrender

00:03:08.910 --> 00:03:11.240 align:middle line:84%
of actually letting
go of the body.

00:03:11.240 --> 00:03:12.350 align:middle line:90%
But that's the big one.

00:03:12.350 --> 00:03:15.220 align:middle line:84%
Before that, I mean, there
are so many things in life

00:03:15.220 --> 00:03:18.470 align:middle line:84%
to surrender to that
will increase your energy

00:03:18.470 --> 00:03:21.370 align:middle line:84%
and make you more flexible,
make you more feminine,

00:03:21.370 --> 00:03:24.490 align:middle line:84%
make you more masculine,
bring you into your true self

00:03:24.490 --> 00:03:28.760 align:middle line:84%
instead of this clenched, tight,
rigid person who's miserable

00:03:28.760 --> 00:03:30.240 align:middle line:90%
inside.

00:03:30.240 --> 00:03:33.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you equate
surrender to little mini

00:03:33.700 --> 00:03:36.010 align:middle line:90%
deaths of the ego at all?

00:03:36.010 --> 00:03:38.130 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Hopefully.

00:03:38.130 --> 00:03:38.760 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:03:38.760 --> 00:03:40.610 align:middle line:84%
The ego is a very
beautiful thing.

00:03:40.610 --> 00:03:44.360 align:middle line:84%
And the ego can help us excel
and all kinds of things,

00:03:44.360 --> 00:03:46.860 align:middle line:90%
but it's not our god.

00:03:46.860 --> 00:03:50.110 align:middle line:84%
We must be in
devotion to humility.

00:03:50.110 --> 00:03:52.990 align:middle line:84%
And when you're stuck
in ego, I can do it.

00:03:52.990 --> 00:03:53.600 align:middle line:90%
It's me.

00:03:53.600 --> 00:03:54.891 align:middle line:90%
I'm the center of the universe.

00:03:54.891 --> 00:03:57.130 align:middle line:84%
You kind of miss the
point of surrender

00:03:57.130 --> 00:03:59.319 align:middle line:84%
because you are not the
center of the universe.

00:03:59.319 --> 00:04:01.360 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But Judith, how
do you get anything done?

00:04:01.360 --> 00:04:03.318 align:middle line:84%
Not saying that you have
to be a control freak,

00:04:03.318 --> 00:04:06.440 align:middle line:84%
but how do you get anything
done if you don't have goals,

00:04:06.440 --> 00:04:09.950 align:middle line:84%
if you don't try to control
the outcome of the goals?

00:04:09.950 --> 00:04:13.020 align:middle line:84%
How do you move
forward in a place

00:04:13.020 --> 00:04:15.584 align:middle line:84%
and be in a place of
surrender at the same time?

00:04:15.584 --> 00:04:17.250 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Well, the
ecstasy of surrender

00:04:17.250 --> 00:04:19.579 align:middle line:84%
and the dance of
surrender is learning

00:04:19.579 --> 00:04:23.580 align:middle line:84%
when to move forward and use
your ego, to use your will

00:04:23.580 --> 00:04:27.710 align:middle line:84%
to go forward but knowing when
to stop and when to let go,

00:04:27.710 --> 00:04:29.370 align:middle line:84%
and then when to
move forward again.

00:04:29.370 --> 00:04:30.220 align:middle line:90%
It's a dance.

00:04:30.220 --> 00:04:31.390 align:middle line:90%
It's a movement.

00:04:31.390 --> 00:04:33.550 align:middle line:90%
It's not one thing or another.

00:04:33.550 --> 00:04:35.700 align:middle line:84%
You learn when to
say, all right, now

00:04:35.700 --> 00:04:38.950 align:middle line:84%
I could be the mountain and
let somebody come to me instead

00:04:38.950 --> 00:04:41.260 align:middle line:84%
of calling, and calling,
and pushing, and pushing.

00:04:41.260 --> 00:04:45.170 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to take a breath
and just sit here and wait.

00:04:45.170 --> 00:04:48.010 align:middle line:84%
Or at other times, you're
going and knocking on doors,

00:04:48.010 --> 00:04:51.450 align:middle line:84%
or you're making calls because
it feels right intuitively.

00:04:51.450 --> 00:04:54.690 align:middle line:84%
So much about surrender is
listening to your intuition,

00:04:54.690 --> 00:04:57.310 align:middle line:84%
the still small voice
inside that will guide you,

00:04:57.310 --> 00:04:58.380 align:middle line:90%
like move forward.

00:04:58.380 --> 00:05:01.730 align:middle line:84%
Your body even feels like
moving forward versus no,

00:05:01.730 --> 00:05:03.900 align:middle line:90%
I'm pushing too hard.

00:05:03.900 --> 00:05:05.460 align:middle line:84%
What I'm teaching
in the book is how

00:05:05.460 --> 00:05:09.410 align:middle line:84%
to get to that point of knowing
when I'm pushing too hard,

00:05:09.410 --> 00:05:11.000 align:middle line:84%
and it's time to
hang back a little.

00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:11.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:05:11.500 --> 00:05:12.670 align:middle line:90%
The pushing hard.

00:05:12.670 --> 00:05:15.290 align:middle line:84%
So tell me about your
evolution with surrender.

00:05:15.290 --> 00:05:18.350 align:middle line:84%
You have many bestselling
books. "Second Sight"

00:05:18.350 --> 00:05:22.020 align:middle line:84%
is a huge book for people where
you talk about your intuition

00:05:22.020 --> 00:05:24.640 align:middle line:84%
and how to recognize so
many different things

00:05:24.640 --> 00:05:26.050 align:middle line:90%
about intuition.

00:05:26.050 --> 00:05:28.780 align:middle line:84%
How did you get to
this place of surrender

00:05:28.780 --> 00:05:32.520 align:middle line:84%
where it comes to your whole
conversation around intuition

00:05:32.520 --> 00:05:33.930 align:middle line:90%
and being a psychologist?

00:05:33.930 --> 00:05:34.930 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:05:34.930 --> 00:05:37.550 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Well, when I
wrote "Second Sight,"

00:05:37.550 --> 00:05:41.320 align:middle line:84%
it was a huge surrender for me
to bring it out into the world

00:05:41.320 --> 00:05:45.330 align:middle line:84%
because I was coming out as
a psychiatrist and a psychic

00:05:45.330 --> 00:05:47.850 align:middle line:84%
or slash intuitive, whatever
you want to call it,

00:05:47.850 --> 00:05:51.510 align:middle line:84%
and I was terrified of what my
medical colleagues would think.

00:05:51.510 --> 00:05:54.840 align:middle line:84%
So my surrender was
trust, turn it over.

00:05:54.840 --> 00:05:56.450 align:middle line:84%
You wrote this book
from your heart.

00:05:56.450 --> 00:05:57.940 align:middle line:90%
You wrote your experience.

00:05:57.940 --> 00:05:59.070 align:middle line:90%
It's the right thing to do.

00:05:59.070 --> 00:06:00.570 align:middle line:90%
Put it out in the world.

00:06:00.570 --> 00:06:01.690 align:middle line:90%
Ah, so scary.

00:06:01.690 --> 00:06:04.255 align:middle line:84%
I'm so afraid of what
people will think.

00:06:04.255 --> 00:06:06.990 align:middle line:84%
So with surrender, it's not
as if you're without fear.

00:06:06.990 --> 00:06:09.100 align:middle line:84%
But I just didn't
let fear dominate me.

00:06:09.100 --> 00:06:11.140 align:middle line:84%
And o the book was
put out in the world,

00:06:11.140 --> 00:06:16.190 align:middle line:84%
and it got such a tremendous
reception for many years.

00:06:16.190 --> 00:06:18.060 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Even from
colleagues as well?

00:06:18.060 --> 00:06:18.760 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Some of my colleagues.

00:06:18.760 --> 00:06:20.140 align:middle line:90%
Yes, many of my colleagues.

00:06:20.140 --> 00:06:22.320 align:middle line:84%
And especially the woman
I'm supervising now

00:06:22.320 --> 00:06:25.490 align:middle line:84%
was reading-- the young psych
resident I'm supervising

00:06:25.490 --> 00:06:28.780 align:middle line:84%
was reading it when she
was undergoing chemo.

00:06:28.780 --> 00:06:29.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:06:29.700 --> 00:06:32.100 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: So to me,
that's very beautiful

00:06:32.100 --> 00:06:35.150 align:middle line:84%
that the opening happens
during a period of crisis.

00:06:35.150 --> 00:06:38.260 align:middle line:84%
And who knows when
you reach for a book.

00:06:38.260 --> 00:06:39.830 align:middle line:90%
It's a magical thing, isn't it?

00:06:39.830 --> 00:06:42.592 align:middle line:84%
The book might fall
out of the bookshelf.

00:06:42.592 --> 00:06:46.920 align:middle line:84%
But my coming out, the surrender
of my fear, and coming out

00:06:46.920 --> 00:06:49.020 align:middle line:84%
as a psychiatrist
and an intuitive

00:06:49.020 --> 00:06:52.130 align:middle line:84%
has been extremely helpful for
other people and other health

00:06:52.130 --> 00:06:54.330 align:middle line:84%
care professionals,
and extremely helpful

00:06:54.330 --> 00:06:57.440 align:middle line:84%
for my freedom in terms
of finding a voice.

00:06:57.440 --> 00:07:00.254 align:middle line:84%
So I had to let go of
that fear and trust

00:07:00.254 --> 00:07:02.420 align:middle line:84%
that there was something
really beautiful about what

00:07:02.420 --> 00:07:04.245 align:middle line:90%
I was doing and something good.

00:07:04.245 --> 00:07:06.370 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Was it more of an
internal struggle for you

00:07:06.370 --> 00:07:08.090 align:middle line:84%
because of the way
that you were raised

00:07:08.090 --> 00:07:11.480 align:middle line:84%
around a professional
family and really

00:07:11.480 --> 00:07:14.550 align:middle line:84%
to go down that trajectory
of being the doctor?

00:07:14.550 --> 00:07:16.550 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Yeah, I think
so because my mother was

00:07:16.550 --> 00:07:19.860 align:middle line:84%
so afraid of what people
would think of me.

00:07:19.860 --> 00:07:21.500 align:middle line:90%
Would I be considered weird?

00:07:21.500 --> 00:07:23.930 align:middle line:84%
Would I be kicked out of
the medical profession?

00:07:23.930 --> 00:07:26.220 align:middle line:84%
Would I be laughed at or
whatever she was afraid of?

00:07:26.220 --> 00:07:28.303 align:middle line:84%
She didn't want me to be
considered, quote, weird.

00:07:28.303 --> 00:07:29.720 align:middle line:90%
That was her worst fear.

00:07:29.720 --> 00:07:31.540 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, as I
wrote in the book,

00:07:31.540 --> 00:07:35.294 align:middle line:84%
I've given up trying to appear
as normal because I'm not.

00:07:35.294 --> 00:07:36.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Good idea.

00:07:36.210 --> 00:07:37.334 align:middle line:90%
We all should give that up.

00:07:37.334 --> 00:07:38.050 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:07:38.050 --> 00:07:38.925 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Give it up.

00:07:38.925 --> 00:07:39.425 align:middle line:90%
I'm not.

00:07:39.425 --> 00:07:41.810 align:middle line:84%
I've always led my own
quirky, different path,

00:07:41.810 --> 00:07:44.280 align:middle line:84%
which I follow with
a lot of passion.

00:07:44.280 --> 00:07:46.170 align:middle line:84%
But I've never gone
the mainstream.

00:07:46.170 --> 00:07:49.030 align:middle line:84%
And I had a mother who
wanted me to go mainstream.

00:07:49.030 --> 00:07:51.020 align:middle line:84%
And so part of my
surrender process

00:07:51.020 --> 00:07:55.650 align:middle line:84%
has been letting go of
what she thinks of it.

00:07:55.650 --> 00:07:57.450 align:middle line:90%
She's on the other side now.

00:07:57.450 --> 00:07:59.870 align:middle line:90%
Or anybody else for that matter.

00:07:59.870 --> 00:08:02.670 align:middle line:84%
So part of surrender-- and
this is hard for people,

00:08:02.670 --> 00:08:04.300 align:middle line:84%
but I teach all
my patients this--

00:08:04.300 --> 00:08:07.290 align:middle line:84%
you have to surrender what
other people think of you.

00:08:07.290 --> 00:08:08.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And want from you.

00:08:08.690 --> 00:08:11.420 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: And want from you
and think is best for you.

00:08:11.420 --> 00:08:13.520 align:middle line:84%
You have to follow
your intuition, what's

00:08:13.520 --> 00:08:14.704 align:middle line:90%
best for yourself.

00:08:14.704 --> 00:08:16.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: OK, let's
talk about that,

00:08:16.120 --> 00:08:18.390 align:middle line:84%
surrendering what other
people think of you.

00:08:18.390 --> 00:08:19.970 align:middle line:84%
I mean, look, when
we're kids, we

00:08:19.970 --> 00:08:21.730 align:middle line:90%
try to fit in out of survival.

00:08:21.730 --> 00:08:24.710 align:middle line:90%
It all starts there in school.

00:08:24.710 --> 00:08:29.690 align:middle line:84%
How do you let go
of that idea of what

00:08:29.690 --> 00:08:31.248 align:middle line:90%
other people think of you?

00:08:31.248 --> 00:08:32.039 align:middle line:90%
How do you do that?

00:08:32.039 --> 00:08:34.570 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: You have to be
very, very true to yourself.

00:08:34.570 --> 00:08:36.549 align:middle line:84%
And you don't do it
in a hostile way,

00:08:36.549 --> 00:08:39.520 align:middle line:84%
but you really weigh the
positives and negatives

00:08:39.520 --> 00:08:41.030 align:middle line:84%
of what people
say and tell them,

00:08:41.030 --> 00:08:42.851 align:middle line:84%
thank you so much
for sharing that.

00:08:42.851 --> 00:08:45.100 align:middle line:84%
Let's say I have a strong
opinion about how you should

00:08:45.100 --> 00:08:47.197 align:middle line:84%
dress, or how you
should lead your life,

00:08:47.197 --> 00:08:49.530 align:middle line:84%
or what person you should
marry-- outrageous things they

00:08:49.530 --> 00:08:51.060 align:middle line:90%
shouldn't even comment on.

00:08:51.060 --> 00:08:54.090 align:middle line:84%
And you just look at them, and
you say thank you for sharing.

00:08:54.090 --> 00:08:56.150 align:middle line:84%
I'll factor that
into my decision.

00:08:56.150 --> 00:08:59.020 align:middle line:84%
And then tune in,
listen to yourself.

00:08:59.020 --> 00:09:02.190 align:middle line:84%
Is this the person that's right
for me, not my mother, not

00:09:02.190 --> 00:09:05.136 align:middle line:84%
my father, not my
teachers, but me?

00:09:05.136 --> 00:09:07.010 align:middle line:84%
Is this the person who's
going to nurture me,

00:09:07.010 --> 00:09:08.950 align:middle line:84%
and I'm going to have
a good relationship?

00:09:08.950 --> 00:09:10.950 align:middle line:84%
You tune in to your
intuition, and you

00:09:10.950 --> 00:09:14.610 align:middle line:84%
go with that instead of the
throngs of relatives saying,

00:09:14.610 --> 00:09:15.830 align:middle line:90%
but he's not this.

00:09:15.830 --> 00:09:16.760 align:middle line:90%
And he's not that.

00:09:16.760 --> 00:09:18.629 align:middle line:90%
No, but he's right for me.

00:09:18.629 --> 00:09:20.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Or if it's not
even a relationship.

00:09:20.420 --> 00:09:22.940 align:middle line:84%
If it's a career
path, or a passion,

00:09:22.940 --> 00:09:25.430 align:middle line:84%
or a hobby to go
back in and say it

00:09:25.430 --> 00:09:27.350 align:middle line:84%
doesn't matter what
people think about me.

00:09:27.350 --> 00:09:29.070 align:middle line:90%
I want to do this.

00:09:29.070 --> 00:09:31.870 align:middle line:84%
And this is what
fills my soul, right?

00:09:31.870 --> 00:09:33.250 align:middle line:84%
Is that what you're
saying to do?

00:09:33.250 --> 00:09:34.330 align:middle line:90%
Surrendering to that.

00:09:34.330 --> 00:09:34.630 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Yes.

00:09:34.630 --> 00:09:36.171 align:middle line:84%
Go for what gives
you the goosebumps.

00:09:36.171 --> 00:09:38.430 align:middle line:84%
As Quincy Jones said in my
book, "Positive Energy,"

00:09:38.430 --> 00:09:39.850 align:middle line:90%
when I interviewed him.

00:09:39.850 --> 00:09:41.100 align:middle line:90%
Listen to the goosebumps.

00:09:41.100 --> 00:09:43.330 align:middle line:84%
He says, he never
goes for projects

00:09:43.330 --> 00:09:47.740 align:middle line:84%
without the goosebumps,
that feeling you get.

00:09:47.740 --> 00:09:49.960 align:middle line:90%
Yes, I'm moving forward.

00:09:49.960 --> 00:09:50.997 align:middle line:90%
And you get a yes.

00:09:50.997 --> 00:09:52.580 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And he's
been very successful.

00:09:52.580 --> 00:09:55.770 align:middle line:84%
And so he listens
to his intuition.

00:09:55.770 --> 00:10:00.730 align:middle line:84%
Tell me about when-- what about
surrender is so liberating?

00:10:00.730 --> 00:10:02.640 align:middle line:90%
What is that feeling?

00:10:02.640 --> 00:10:04.100 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Just
exhale and feel how

00:10:04.100 --> 00:10:05.870 align:middle line:84%
that surrender--
that's a surrender.

00:10:05.870 --> 00:10:07.834 align:middle line:84%
Instead of holding
your breath, you're ah.

00:10:07.834 --> 00:10:09.250 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Shoulders
are raised and--

00:10:09.250 --> 00:10:11.083 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Down come the
shoulders, you know,

00:10:11.083 --> 00:10:13.600 align:middle line:90%
out go the arms.

00:10:13.600 --> 00:10:14.780 align:middle line:90%
You're radiant.

00:10:14.780 --> 00:10:15.740 align:middle line:90%
You're moving.

00:10:15.740 --> 00:10:18.720 align:middle line:84%
You're flowing instead
of rigid in your head

00:10:18.720 --> 00:10:21.170 align:middle line:84%
because unfortunately, a
lot of really smart people

00:10:21.170 --> 00:10:22.830 align:middle line:90%
just live up in their head.

00:10:22.830 --> 00:10:26.510 align:middle line:84%
So when they age, it's not
easy for their bodies to age

00:10:26.510 --> 00:10:29.080 align:middle line:84%
because they've never put
the energy into their bodies.

00:10:29.080 --> 00:10:30.980 align:middle line:84%
And when you
surrender as a woman,

00:10:30.980 --> 00:10:33.980 align:middle line:84%
let's say, you surrender
to your feminine

00:10:33.980 --> 00:10:35.780 align:middle line:84%
and you surrender
to your masculine.

00:10:35.780 --> 00:10:36.830 align:middle line:90%
You go back and forth.

00:10:36.830 --> 00:10:40.810 align:middle line:84%
Often, in career things with
me, I get into my masculine

00:10:40.810 --> 00:10:43.450 align:middle line:84%
because I have to organize
things, I have to send people--

00:10:43.450 --> 00:10:44.520 align:middle line:90%
but that's OK.

00:10:44.520 --> 00:10:47.950 align:middle line:84%
But I don't stay in that
masculine all the time.

00:10:47.950 --> 00:10:51.470 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What do you
do for your feminine?

00:10:51.470 --> 00:10:53.020 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Well, I
have a relationship

00:10:53.020 --> 00:10:56.050 align:middle line:84%
that nurtures that, which
is very, very helpful.

00:10:56.050 --> 00:10:57.990 align:middle line:90%
I go barefoot.

00:10:57.990 --> 00:11:02.350 align:middle line:84%
It's called earthing, bringing
the energy of the earth

00:11:02.350 --> 00:11:03.500 align:middle line:90%
into my feet.

00:11:03.500 --> 00:11:05.410 align:middle line:90%
I get massages.

00:11:05.410 --> 00:11:07.310 align:middle line:90%
I'm in my body.

00:11:07.310 --> 00:11:09.280 align:middle line:90%
I feel my body.

00:11:09.280 --> 00:11:10.740 align:middle line:90%
I'm very in touch with nature.

00:11:10.740 --> 00:11:11.800 align:middle line:90%
I dance.

00:11:11.800 --> 00:11:13.710 align:middle line:90%
I do movement.

00:11:13.710 --> 00:11:17.170 align:middle line:84%
But it's a conscious shift,
surrendering to your masculine.

00:11:17.170 --> 00:11:19.640 align:middle line:84%
When you're in that
mode-- I find it very hard

00:11:19.640 --> 00:11:21.480 align:middle line:84%
to be in the
feminine mode and do

00:11:21.480 --> 00:11:24.550 align:middle line:84%
a lot of my work, especially
organizational work.

00:11:24.550 --> 00:11:27.127 align:middle line:84%
It's not anything the feminine
in me really wants to do.

00:11:27.127 --> 00:11:28.960 align:middle line:84%
I just do other things
like go to the beach.

00:11:28.960 --> 00:11:30.626 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But you're
saying, it's OK to be

00:11:30.626 --> 00:11:33.630 align:middle line:84%
in that place of masculine
as a female body.

00:11:33.630 --> 00:11:38.120 align:middle line:84%
It's OK for men to be in a place
of feminine as a male body.

00:11:38.120 --> 00:11:41.190 align:middle line:90%
And it's the balance of the two.

00:11:41.190 --> 00:11:45.025 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter if you have
that experience, especially

00:11:45.025 --> 00:11:47.820 align:middle line:84%
the male body, if you have
that experience of feeling

00:11:47.820 --> 00:11:51.210 align:middle line:84%
the feminine, feeling that
receiving side, feeling that.

00:11:51.210 --> 00:11:54.581 align:middle line:84%
You can have both, no matter
what kind of body you have,

00:11:54.581 --> 00:11:55.080 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:11:55.080 --> 00:11:56.163 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Yes, absolutely.

00:11:56.163 --> 00:11:58.220 align:middle line:84%
Well, we all started
as X chromosomes.

00:11:58.220 --> 00:12:00.599 align:middle line:90%
So we all started as feminine.

00:12:00.599 --> 00:12:01.640 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting, yes.

00:12:01.640 --> 00:12:02.348 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: I know.

00:12:02.348 --> 00:12:06.710 align:middle line:84%
So-- and many men are afraid
of embracing the feminine

00:12:06.710 --> 00:12:08.960 align:middle line:90%
in themselves.

00:12:08.960 --> 00:12:12.530 align:middle line:84%
And women often embrace
masculine a little bit easier.

00:12:12.530 --> 00:12:13.427 align:middle line:90%
But we're both.

00:12:13.427 --> 00:12:15.260 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Society has a
whole thing around it.

00:12:15.260 --> 00:12:15.885 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Yeah.

00:12:15.885 --> 00:12:16.600 align:middle line:90%
But it's both.

00:12:16.600 --> 00:12:18.740 align:middle line:84%
Surrendering-- there's
a whole section

00:12:18.740 --> 00:12:20.960 align:middle line:84%
in the book on
surrendering to sexuality,

00:12:20.960 --> 00:12:23.580 align:middle line:84%
surrendering to the
divinity of your body,

00:12:23.580 --> 00:12:27.684 align:middle line:84%
and how to live in your body and
not just live up in your head.

00:12:27.684 --> 00:12:29.850 align:middle line:84%
It's when you live in your
body, you're surrendered.

00:12:29.850 --> 00:12:32.250 align:middle line:84%
And by that, I mean
bringing your consciousness

00:12:32.250 --> 00:12:34.580 align:middle line:84%
down to your body,
asking yourself

00:12:34.580 --> 00:12:38.350 align:middle line:84%
what does my body feel about
this person or this job?

00:12:38.350 --> 00:12:39.280 align:middle line:90%
How do you feel?

00:12:39.280 --> 00:12:40.750 align:middle line:90%
I'm always talking to my body.

00:12:40.750 --> 00:12:42.930 align:middle line:90%
I'm going, how are you in here?

00:12:42.930 --> 00:12:44.010 align:middle line:90%
I'm not so good.

00:12:44.010 --> 00:12:45.220 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:12:45.220 --> 00:12:47.610 align:middle line:90%
Inner dialogue.

00:12:47.610 --> 00:12:49.550 align:middle line:84%
The body is the
divine instrument,

00:12:49.550 --> 00:12:52.010 align:middle line:90%
a divine intuitive instrument.

00:12:52.010 --> 00:12:54.060 align:middle line:84%
And so we need to
really live in it.

00:12:54.060 --> 00:12:57.120 align:middle line:84%
And part of surrendering
is surrendering to the fact

00:12:57.120 --> 00:12:59.070 align:middle line:84%
that you have a
body and nurturing

00:12:59.070 --> 00:13:02.280 align:middle line:84%
that body with vibrant
energy as much as you can.

00:13:02.280 --> 00:13:05.990 align:middle line:84%
Yoga as we were talking,
exercise, meditation

00:13:05.990 --> 00:13:08.840 align:middle line:84%
brings the vital
energies into the body.

00:13:08.840 --> 00:13:11.130 align:middle line:84%
Just don't sit at
a desk and work,

00:13:11.130 --> 00:13:13.810 align:middle line:84%
and stay on your computer,
and sleep, and go home,

00:13:13.810 --> 00:13:15.330 align:middle line:84%
and wake up, and
do the same thing.

00:13:15.330 --> 00:13:16.288 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: All over again.

00:13:16.288 --> 00:13:19.150 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: At least keep a
yoga mat by your computer

00:13:19.150 --> 00:13:20.930 align:middle line:84%
and just get into
some stretching

00:13:20.930 --> 00:13:22.897 align:middle line:84%
pose, which is a
form of surrender.

00:13:22.897 --> 00:13:23.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:13:23.730 --> 00:13:26.640 align:middle line:84%
Yes, stretching is a
wonderful form of surrender.

00:13:26.640 --> 00:13:27.500 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Oh, it is.

00:13:27.500 --> 00:13:30.574 align:middle line:84%
Stretching is so beautiful,
even little stretches.

00:13:30.574 --> 00:13:31.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We're going
to take a look

00:13:31.990 --> 00:13:34.670 align:middle line:84%
at a video here of
Judith's Ted Talk.

00:13:34.670 --> 00:13:37.640 align:middle line:84%
It's received over a
half a million views.

00:13:37.640 --> 00:13:39.890 align:middle line:84%
Take a look at the
beginning of her Ted Talk.

