>>ORLOFF: You know, I
have a confession to make.

00:14:00.180 --> 00:14:04.970 align:middle line:84%
I lost control, but in
the most wonderful way.

00:14:04.970 --> 00:14:08.010 align:middle line:84%
Before the sacred hours
of seeing patients,

00:14:08.010 --> 00:14:13.480 align:middle line:84%
before writing, I just put
my arms out and danced.

00:14:13.480 --> 00:14:16.420 align:middle line:84%
My body just moved
to Dylan's "Sad Eyed

00:14:16.420 --> 00:14:17.700 align:middle line:90%
Lady of the Low Lands."

00:14:17.700 --> 00:14:20.610 align:middle line:90%
Spontaneous, joyful movements.

00:14:20.610 --> 00:14:25.330 align:middle line:84%
No arguing, no resisting,
no holding back.

00:14:25.330 --> 00:14:28.090 align:middle line:90%
I just let go.

00:14:28.090 --> 00:14:30.025 align:middle line:84%
This is the ecstasy
of surrender.

00:14:30.025 --> 00:14:32.830 align:middle line:90%


00:14:32.830 --> 00:14:34.880 align:middle line:84%
Today your life is going
to get better learning

00:14:34.880 --> 00:14:36.380 align:middle line:90%
about surrender.

00:14:36.380 --> 00:14:40.470 align:middle line:84%
As a physician and as a woman,
this is so important to me.

00:14:40.470 --> 00:14:42.310 align:middle line:84%
It's what I want
the most in my life,

00:14:42.310 --> 00:14:46.160 align:middle line:84%
to be able to flow with things
and not fight, and not resist,

00:14:46.160 --> 00:14:49.450 align:middle line:84%
and not hold back, and not
always over think things.

00:14:49.450 --> 00:14:52.010 align:middle line:84%
It's such a joy to
be able to flow.

00:14:52.010 --> 00:14:53.690 align:middle line:90%
Now what is surrender?

00:14:53.690 --> 00:14:57.900 align:middle line:84%
In Sanskrit, surrender
is samprada, the ability

00:14:57.900 --> 00:15:02.910 align:middle line:84%
to give yourself wholly to
something, to flow like water,

00:15:02.910 --> 00:15:05.810 align:middle line:90%
to not force things.

00:15:05.810 --> 00:15:07.720 align:middle line:84%
I'm defining it as
the grace of letting

00:15:07.720 --> 00:15:10.420 align:middle line:84%
go at the right
moment, of knowing how

00:15:10.420 --> 00:15:14.130 align:middle line:84%
to let go when the time is
right without torturing yourself

00:15:14.130 --> 00:15:17.350 align:middle line:84%
with self-doubt or
overthinking things.

00:15:17.350 --> 00:15:20.510 align:middle line:90%
How many of you overthink?

00:15:20.510 --> 00:15:23.370 align:middle line:84%
How many of you torture
yourself with self-doubt?

00:15:23.370 --> 00:15:25.050 align:middle line:90%
That's very common.

00:15:25.050 --> 00:15:27.900 align:middle line:84%
But surrender allows
you not to do that.

00:15:27.900 --> 00:15:30.220 align:middle line:84%
Imagine a life where
you're not doing that,

00:15:30.220 --> 00:15:33.150 align:middle line:84%
and you're able to flow
more with everything

00:15:33.150 --> 00:15:35.470 align:middle line:90%
and have more peace in life.

00:15:35.470 --> 00:15:38.720 align:middle line:84%
That is the great
joy of surrender.

00:15:38.720 --> 00:15:41.340 align:middle line:90%
Now how surrendered are you?

00:15:41.340 --> 00:15:44.500 align:middle line:90%
Let me ask you a few questions.

00:15:44.500 --> 00:15:50.330 align:middle line:84%
Do you recognize that you
cannot control everything?

00:15:50.330 --> 00:15:51.820 align:middle line:90%
How many of you?

00:15:51.820 --> 00:15:54.580 align:middle line:90%
I hope you do.

00:15:54.580 --> 00:15:56.760 align:middle line:84%
If you've tried your
best with something,

00:15:56.760 --> 00:15:59.690 align:middle line:84%
and you've given a project
let's say all of your effort,

00:15:59.690 --> 00:16:03.820 align:middle line:84%
are you able to back off
and not torture yourself

00:16:03.820 --> 00:16:07.110 align:middle line:84%
with self-doubt and just give
the project some breathing

00:16:07.110 --> 00:16:07.720 align:middle line:90%
room?

00:16:07.720 --> 00:16:10.520 align:middle line:84%
How many of you are
able to do that?

00:16:10.520 --> 00:16:12.730 align:middle line:90%
All right, wonderful.

00:16:12.730 --> 00:16:16.620 align:middle line:84%
Can you admit that
you are not right?

00:16:16.620 --> 00:16:18.800 align:middle line:84%
Do you have to be
right all the time,

00:16:18.800 --> 00:16:22.610 align:middle line:84%
or can you apologize,
can you compromise,

00:16:22.610 --> 00:16:25.680 align:middle line:84%
can you let go of
the need to be right?

00:16:25.680 --> 00:16:26.180 align:middle line:90%
Oh good.

00:16:26.180 --> 00:16:27.465 align:middle line:90%
I see one hand.

00:16:27.465 --> 00:16:27.964 align:middle line:90%
Hahaha.

00:16:27.964 --> 00:16:30.660 align:middle line:90%


00:16:30.660 --> 00:16:33.480 align:middle line:84%
Can you be spontaneous
and not have

00:16:33.480 --> 00:16:36.240 align:middle line:84%
to plan every single thing
down to the last detail?

00:16:36.240 --> 00:16:38.760 align:middle line:90%


00:16:38.760 --> 00:16:40.780 align:middle line:90%
Can you enjoy life?

00:16:40.780 --> 00:16:47.800 align:middle line:84%
Can you stop long enough to let
that enjoyment in an absorb it?

00:16:47.800 --> 00:16:52.800 align:middle line:84%
Isn't that what it's all about,
just letting that enjoyment in?

00:16:52.800 --> 00:16:54.860 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
point of surrender.

00:16:54.860 --> 00:16:57.120 align:middle line:84%
As life goes by so
quickly, you know,

00:16:57.120 --> 00:17:00.230 align:middle line:84%
you want to take advantage
of every single moment.

00:17:00.230 --> 00:17:03.740 align:middle line:84%
And to do that, you have
to be able to let go.

00:17:03.740 --> 00:17:06.660 align:middle line:84%
Now what stands in
the way of surrender?

00:17:06.660 --> 00:17:08.030 align:middle line:90%
In my life, I know this well.

00:17:08.030 --> 00:17:10.440 align:middle line:84%
It's when I want
something too much,

00:17:10.440 --> 00:17:12.390 align:middle line:90%
when I'm over invested in it.

00:17:12.390 --> 00:17:14.540 align:middle line:84%
When I really want
something a lot,

00:17:14.540 --> 00:17:16.460 align:middle line:90%
that can clog the circuits.

00:17:16.460 --> 00:17:18.329 align:middle line:84%
And so when you want
something too much,

00:17:18.329 --> 00:17:21.190 align:middle line:84%
that's a sign you need
to just back off a little

00:17:21.190 --> 00:17:24.230 align:middle line:84%
so you don't get
overbearing with it.

00:17:24.230 --> 00:17:26.530 align:middle line:84%
Another thing is
anxiety and fear.

00:17:26.530 --> 00:17:28.770 align:middle line:84%
When you clench, when
you get into a fear

00:17:28.770 --> 00:17:33.610 align:middle line:84%
mode or an anxious mode, that
stops you from surrendering.

00:17:33.610 --> 00:17:38.040 align:middle line:84%
What fascinates me is how
hard it is for most of us

00:17:38.040 --> 00:17:39.790 align:middle line:90%
to surrender.

00:17:39.790 --> 00:17:41.260 align:middle line:90%
Do you realize how hard it is?

00:17:41.260 --> 00:17:43.140 align:middle line:84%
But when you think
about it, you need

00:17:43.140 --> 00:17:48.369 align:middle line:84%
to surrender to delight
in an orgasm, don't you?

00:17:48.369 --> 00:17:50.535 align:middle line:84%
If you don't surrender, not
much is going to happen.

00:17:50.535 --> 00:17:54.330 align:middle line:90%


00:17:54.330 --> 00:17:56.070 align:middle line:90%
Or a good night's sleep.

00:17:56.070 --> 00:17:58.680 align:middle line:84%
Every night, you need to
surrender when you go to sleep,

00:17:58.680 --> 00:18:02.080 align:middle line:84%
otherwise you'll be tossing
and turning all night.

00:18:02.080 --> 00:18:06.070 align:middle line:84%
You need to surrender with a
good belly laugh or a good cry.

00:18:06.070 --> 00:18:08.640 align:middle line:84%
I love the healing
power of tears.

00:18:08.640 --> 00:18:12.480 align:middle line:84%
When you hold back tears,
that's not good for your system.

00:18:12.480 --> 00:18:14.750 align:middle line:84%
And so surrendering
to tears, just

00:18:14.750 --> 00:18:17.170 align:middle line:84%
letting it flow, or any
emotion, such as grief

00:18:17.170 --> 00:18:19.850 align:middle line:84%
when you experience
loss, that is

00:18:19.850 --> 00:18:24.140 align:middle line:84%
when you really are
flowing with life.

00:18:24.140 --> 00:18:28.200 align:middle line:84%
And so what I want to say is
that we need to bring surrender

00:18:28.200 --> 00:18:31.900 align:middle line:84%
into other aspects of our
life where the downside isn't

00:18:31.900 --> 00:18:35.060 align:middle line:84%
so obvious, such as
hijacking pleasure,

00:18:35.060 --> 00:18:38.160 align:middle line:84%
because if something immediately
hijacked pleasure for you,

00:18:38.160 --> 00:18:40.835 align:middle line:84%
you would think twice
about it, hopefully.

00:18:40.835 --> 00:18:42.710 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: OK, I want to
ask you about this part

00:18:42.710 --> 00:18:45.232 align:middle line:84%
about pushing hard,
about pushing so hard,

00:18:45.232 --> 00:18:46.440 align:middle line:90%
and pushing yourself so hard.

00:18:46.440 --> 00:18:49.850 align:middle line:84%
When you've set up things around
you, and you're exhausted,

00:18:49.850 --> 00:18:51.920 align:middle line:84%
and you don't want
to push, but you

00:18:51.920 --> 00:18:54.340 align:middle line:84%
can't stop because
of all the situations

00:18:54.340 --> 00:18:59.200 align:middle line:84%
you've set up around you, how
can you take that break from--

00:18:59.200 --> 00:19:01.130 align:middle line:84%
and still fulfill
your commitments?

00:19:01.130 --> 00:19:04.300 align:middle line:84%
How can you surrender
to the commitments

00:19:04.300 --> 00:19:05.929 align:middle line:84%
that you have, I
guess, is my question.

00:19:05.929 --> 00:19:08.095 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Well, one thing
I've noticed about myself,

00:19:08.095 --> 00:19:12.230 align:middle line:84%
if I'm pushing too hard, I start
to get anxious and exhausted.

00:19:12.230 --> 00:19:14.500 align:middle line:90%
So I notice that in myself.

00:19:14.500 --> 00:19:16.730 align:middle line:84%
And then I get
impatient with people,

00:19:16.730 --> 00:19:19.810 align:middle line:84%
and I'm not really that
great in communicating.

00:19:19.810 --> 00:19:21.990 align:middle line:84%
So I try and catch
that in myself

00:19:21.990 --> 00:19:25.240 align:middle line:84%
in the beginning compassionately
and say, OK, you're

00:19:25.240 --> 00:19:25.840 align:middle line:90%
there again.

00:19:25.840 --> 00:19:27.580 align:middle line:90%
Take a little break.

00:19:27.580 --> 00:19:29.530 align:middle line:84%
So I'll take a three
minute meditation,

00:19:29.530 --> 00:19:32.090 align:middle line:84%
which I talk about in the
book, a three minute heart

00:19:32.090 --> 00:19:35.760 align:middle line:84%
meditation where it's
just time out, reset.

00:19:35.760 --> 00:19:37.600 align:middle line:90%
I need to be reset here.

00:19:37.600 --> 00:19:39.420 align:middle line:84%
Each person has to
reset themselves

00:19:39.420 --> 00:19:41.500 align:middle line:84%
when they get off as
quickly as possible.

00:19:41.500 --> 00:19:42.490 align:middle line:90%
So I sit.

00:19:42.490 --> 00:19:44.550 align:middle line:90%
I close my eyes.

00:19:44.550 --> 00:19:45.960 align:middle line:90%
I take a breath.

00:19:45.960 --> 00:19:48.450 align:middle line:90%
I tune in to my heart.

00:19:48.450 --> 00:19:51.740 align:middle line:84%
And I come back to my
center, and I feel spirit.

00:19:51.740 --> 00:19:53.900 align:middle line:90%
And so I realign myself.

00:19:53.900 --> 00:19:56.610 align:middle line:84%
Just three minutes, only
three minutes, no longer.

00:19:56.610 --> 00:19:58.690 align:middle line:84%
It's just a very time
limited meditation

00:19:58.690 --> 00:20:01.130 align:middle line:84%
I suggest for people,
a quick tuneup.

00:20:01.130 --> 00:20:02.284 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Why no longer?

00:20:02.284 --> 00:20:04.450 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: That's not the
purpose of this meditation.

00:20:04.450 --> 00:20:07.490 align:middle line:84%
It's just this a quick
tuneup in a busy life.

00:20:07.490 --> 00:20:10.970 align:middle line:84%
It's not 45 minutes of
meditation, not a quiet time.

00:20:10.970 --> 00:20:12.500 align:middle line:90%
It's in the midst of chaos.

00:20:12.500 --> 00:20:15.620 align:middle line:84%
When you get thrown off, how do
you come back together quickly.

00:20:15.620 --> 00:20:18.090 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yes, so you can
have good conversations

00:20:18.090 --> 00:20:20.310 align:middle line:84%
and relationships and not
be so short with people.

00:20:20.310 --> 00:20:22.090 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: And I
blow it because when

00:20:22.090 --> 00:20:24.020 align:middle line:84%
you get into that
anxious state, you know,

00:20:24.020 --> 00:20:25.520 align:middle line:84%
I know I say all
these things that I

00:20:25.520 --> 00:20:29.950 align:middle line:90%
wish I could take back later.

00:20:29.950 --> 00:20:31.580 align:middle line:90%
It's very common.

00:20:31.580 --> 00:20:33.890 align:middle line:90%
That's why I'm bringing it up.

00:20:33.890 --> 00:20:35.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And then, I regret
those conversations.

00:20:35.860 --> 00:20:38.020 align:middle line:90%
I was short with that person.

00:20:38.020 --> 00:20:40.450 align:middle line:84%
I didn't have compassion
in that situation.

00:20:40.450 --> 00:20:42.170 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, absolutely.

00:20:42.170 --> 00:20:44.480 align:middle line:84%
Well, there's three
types of surrender

00:20:44.480 --> 00:20:46.720 align:middle line:90%
that you talk about in the book.

00:20:46.720 --> 00:20:48.240 align:middle line:90%
The first one is crisis.

00:20:48.240 --> 00:20:51.770 align:middle line:84%
So when there's a
time of total crisis,

00:20:51.770 --> 00:20:53.830 align:middle line:84%
how do you surrender
in that moment?

00:20:53.830 --> 00:20:55.660 align:middle line:90%
What are you surrendering to?

00:20:55.660 --> 00:20:57.700 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Well, crisis,
the Chinese ideogram,

00:20:57.700 --> 00:21:00.360 align:middle line:90%
crisis equals opportunity.

00:21:00.360 --> 00:21:03.610 align:middle line:84%
So if you look at
crisis as opportunity,

00:21:03.610 --> 00:21:05.460 align:middle line:90%
that's the time to surrender.

00:21:05.460 --> 00:21:09.070 align:middle line:84%
And oftentimes, people are
forced to submit to surrender.

00:21:09.070 --> 00:21:11.045 align:middle line:84%
I had a patient who
O.D.ed on cocaine

00:21:11.045 --> 00:21:13.060 align:middle line:84%
and ended up in
the emergency room

00:21:13.060 --> 00:21:16.180 align:middle line:84%
for the 10 millionth
time near death's door.

00:21:16.180 --> 00:21:18.390 align:middle line:90%
Finally, I've had enough.

00:21:18.390 --> 00:21:19.460 align:middle line:90%
I surrender.

00:21:19.460 --> 00:21:22.300 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to a 12 step program.

00:21:22.300 --> 00:21:23.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So that moment.

00:21:23.980 --> 00:21:25.920 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes we create
those for ourselves

00:21:25.920 --> 00:21:29.490 align:middle line:84%
so that we can hit the
bottom and have a real excuse

00:21:29.490 --> 00:21:31.150 align:middle line:90%
to be able to surrender.

00:21:31.150 --> 00:21:33.020 align:middle line:84%
But the idea is not to
get that far, right?

00:21:33.020 --> 00:21:34.478 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: It's not
to get that far.

00:21:34.478 --> 00:21:37.210 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes, illness could
be a prompt to surrender.

00:21:37.210 --> 00:21:40.290 align:middle line:84%
The crisis of illness makes
you reevaluate everything

00:21:40.290 --> 00:21:43.250 align:middle line:84%
in your life, what's
important, in a second.

00:21:43.250 --> 00:21:45.870 align:middle line:84%
When you become ill,
your reality shifts.

00:21:45.870 --> 00:21:47.620 align:middle line:84%
And so suddenly,
what's important?

00:21:47.620 --> 00:21:49.060 align:middle line:84%
Where do I want
to give my energy?

00:21:49.060 --> 00:21:50.351 align:middle line:90%
Where can't I waste it anymore.

00:21:50.351 --> 00:21:53.500 align:middle line:84%
You can't waste it
worrying and being in fear.

00:21:53.500 --> 00:21:56.000 align:middle line:84%
You have to be positive
in order to heal.

00:21:56.000 --> 00:21:59.470 align:middle line:84%
So illness is a crisis that
I've seen as a physician really

00:21:59.470 --> 00:22:02.820 align:middle line:84%
aligns people with--
it can align people

00:22:02.820 --> 00:22:06.650 align:middle line:84%
with their inner needs
and their purpose.

00:22:06.650 --> 00:22:11.140 align:middle line:84%
But as you said, you can wait
for a crisis, but I wouldn't.

00:22:11.140 --> 00:22:11.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's hard.

00:22:11.900 --> 00:22:16.100 align:middle line:84%
I mean to push yourself to that
limit is-- and I've been there.

00:22:16.100 --> 00:22:18.820 align:middle line:84%
I've been sick where I've had
to monitor every single thought

00:22:18.820 --> 00:22:21.260 align:middle line:84%
because the negative ones
drain the energy when

00:22:21.260 --> 00:22:23.220 align:middle line:90%
my energy is just limited.

00:22:23.220 --> 00:22:26.230 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, it definitely
puts you into that place.

00:22:26.230 --> 00:22:28.970 align:middle line:84%
But the idea is not to get
there and to listen to the signs

00:22:28.970 --> 00:22:31.930 align:middle line:84%
beforehand so that you
don't continue to push.

00:22:31.930 --> 00:22:36.410 align:middle line:84%
Another one is surrendering
anxiety and fear.

00:22:36.410 --> 00:22:38.580 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Oh, that's so
big just for everyone

00:22:38.580 --> 00:22:41.000 align:middle line:84%
to make a commitment
on a daily basis

00:22:41.000 --> 00:22:43.930 align:middle line:84%
to try and surrender
anxiety and fear,

00:22:43.930 --> 00:22:47.010 align:middle line:84%
and instead come from
the heart and trust where

00:22:47.010 --> 00:22:49.260 align:middle line:90%
your intuition is leading you.

00:22:49.260 --> 00:22:50.664 align:middle line:90%
That's not fear or anxiety.

00:22:50.664 --> 00:22:52.080 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Give me
an example of what

00:22:52.080 --> 00:22:54.910 align:middle line:84%
that means, surrendering
to anxiety or fear.

00:22:54.910 --> 00:22:56.820 align:middle line:90%
What's an example of that?

00:22:56.820 --> 00:22:59.140 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Well, let's say
you're after a career.

00:22:59.140 --> 00:23:01.950 align:middle line:84%
You're really looking for
a career in, let's say,

00:23:01.950 --> 00:23:02.980 align:middle line:90%
the fashion industry.

00:23:02.980 --> 00:23:04.550 align:middle line:84%
And you want to go
for that career,

00:23:04.550 --> 00:23:07.190 align:middle line:84%
but you have all kinds of fear
that you're not this enough

00:23:07.190 --> 00:23:09.400 align:middle line:84%
or not that enough, and
so you stay in your room,

00:23:09.400 --> 00:23:12.210 align:middle line:84%
and you don't make any
calls, and you don't go out

00:23:12.210 --> 00:23:15.480 align:middle line:84%
as opposed to oh my god,
this feels so good inside.

00:23:15.480 --> 00:23:16.950 align:middle line:90%
This is where I belong.

00:23:16.950 --> 00:23:18.210 align:middle line:90%
And I'm scared.

00:23:18.210 --> 00:23:20.690 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to make
the call anyways.

00:23:20.690 --> 00:23:24.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So surrendering to that
fear and diving into it, right?

00:23:24.240 --> 00:23:27.196 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Well, diving into
it but not letting it stop you

00:23:27.196 --> 00:23:28.570 align:middle line:84%
by saying, all
right, I'm afraid.

00:23:28.570 --> 00:23:29.870 align:middle line:90%
But so what?

00:23:29.870 --> 00:23:30.820 align:middle line:90%
Everybody's afraid.

00:23:30.820 --> 00:23:33.700 align:middle line:84%
You have no idea how much
fear is in everybody.

00:23:33.700 --> 00:23:34.920 align:middle line:90%
I've walked through things.

00:23:34.920 --> 00:23:36.160 align:middle line:90%
I am so scared.

00:23:36.160 --> 00:23:40.320 align:middle line:84%
When I did that Ted Talk, I was
afraid to the very last minute.

00:23:40.320 --> 00:23:42.550 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, usually,
my fear lifts before then.

00:23:42.550 --> 00:23:44.230 align:middle line:84%
The very last
minute I was afraid

00:23:44.230 --> 00:23:46.510 align:middle line:84%
because you have to
stand in a little circle

00:23:46.510 --> 00:23:47.777 align:middle line:90%
when you do the Ted Talk.

00:23:47.777 --> 00:23:49.360 align:middle line:84%
And I couldn't move
out of the circle.

00:23:49.360 --> 00:23:51.264 align:middle line:84%
And it was inhibiting
my activity.

00:23:51.264 --> 00:23:52.680 align:middle line:84%
So I didn't know
if I could do it.

00:23:52.680 --> 00:23:56.030 align:middle line:84%
But the minute I got
up there, it lifted.

00:23:56.030 --> 00:23:57.169 align:middle line:90%
And I was able to--

00:23:57.169 --> 00:23:58.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You looked comfortable.

00:23:58.460 --> 00:23:59.580 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Yeah, comfortable.

00:23:59.580 --> 00:24:01.830 align:middle line:84%
I was able to-- because I
connected with the audience,

00:24:01.830 --> 00:24:05.030 align:middle line:84%
and that always aligns me, when
I'm connecting with people.

00:24:05.030 --> 00:24:06.600 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What about
that surrendering

00:24:06.600 --> 00:24:08.250 align:middle line:90%
to the fear of public speaking?

00:24:08.250 --> 00:24:10.150 align:middle line:84%
Where did you put
your attention?

00:24:10.150 --> 00:24:12.860 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Not on myself.

00:24:12.860 --> 00:24:14.390 align:middle line:90%
I'm not in my personal self.

00:24:14.390 --> 00:24:15.490 align:middle line:90%
I don't think about me.

00:24:15.490 --> 00:24:19.170 align:middle line:84%
I think about the audience
and what I could give to them.

00:24:19.170 --> 00:24:20.380 align:middle line:90%
And then I'm in the flow.

00:24:20.380 --> 00:24:22.570 align:middle line:90%
Then I'm really grooving.

00:24:22.570 --> 00:24:24.920 align:middle line:84%
But if I got up when I spoke
in front of, let's say,

00:24:24.920 --> 00:24:27.380 align:middle line:84%
hundreds of people, and
I was thinking oh my god,

00:24:27.380 --> 00:24:28.980 align:middle line:84%
I'm up here-- I
don't think about me.

00:24:28.980 --> 00:24:29.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh god no.

00:24:29.730 --> 00:24:30.820 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, that would be awful.

00:24:30.820 --> 00:24:34.490 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: It's surrendering
my self and my personal self

00:24:34.490 --> 00:24:38.290 align:middle line:84%
and just feeling the ecstasy
of the flow of speaking

00:24:38.290 --> 00:24:41.440 align:middle line:84%
and the audience that you
feel when you do your show.

00:24:41.440 --> 00:24:44.830 align:middle line:84%
It's just so beautiful to
be able to give up your ego

00:24:44.830 --> 00:24:46.850 align:middle line:90%
and just be in the energy.

00:24:46.850 --> 00:24:48.470 align:middle line:90%
That's a surrender.

00:24:48.470 --> 00:24:49.100 align:middle line:90%
It really is.

00:24:49.100 --> 00:24:51.058 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I love the word
ecstasy, because it is;

00:24:51.058 --> 00:24:54.310 align:middle line:84%
it's that pure
bliss of surrender.

00:24:54.310 --> 00:24:55.370 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Of connection.

00:24:55.370 --> 00:24:58.770 align:middle line:84%
When you can let go of your
fear even for a moment.

00:24:58.770 --> 00:25:03.200 align:middle line:84%
Just the bliss of connection,
the ecstasy of I'm with you.

00:25:03.200 --> 00:25:04.700 align:middle line:90%
And I could be with you totally.

00:25:04.700 --> 00:25:05.630 align:middle line:90%
I'm nowhere else.

00:25:05.630 --> 00:25:08.110 align:middle line:84%
Surrendering is
being in the now.

00:25:08.110 --> 00:25:12.150 align:middle line:84%
And that is the key to ecstasy
when nothing else intrudes,

00:25:12.150 --> 00:25:15.500 align:middle line:84%
just me and you here,
doing this show,

00:25:15.500 --> 00:25:18.680 align:middle line:84%
having fun, feeling the
ecstasy of this connection.

00:25:18.680 --> 00:25:20.080 align:middle line:90%
And then it builds.

00:25:20.080 --> 00:25:23.350 align:middle line:84%
Then you start to really feel
almost altered states from it.

00:25:23.350 --> 00:25:25.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And I'm grateful for it.

00:25:25.010 --> 00:25:27.120 align:middle line:90%
I'm grateful for our connection.

00:25:27.120 --> 00:25:30.230 align:middle line:84%
I'm grateful for our
female to femaleness.

00:25:30.230 --> 00:25:31.770 align:middle line:84%
Whatever it is, it
comes out of it.

00:25:31.770 --> 00:25:33.550 align:middle line:90%
It rises out of it.

00:25:33.550 --> 00:25:35.540 align:middle line:84%
So that's the other--
another part of surrender

00:25:35.540 --> 00:25:38.280 align:middle line:90%
is surrendering to what is.

00:25:38.280 --> 00:25:40.050 align:middle line:90%
This is what is.

00:25:40.050 --> 00:25:42.037 align:middle line:84%
Being out in nature,
surrendering to that.

00:25:42.037 --> 00:25:43.870 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: This is all
you have, this moment.

00:25:43.870 --> 00:25:45.190 align:middle line:90%
Everyone is watching it.

00:25:45.190 --> 00:25:46.550 align:middle line:90%
This is your moment.

00:25:46.550 --> 00:25:48.740 align:middle line:90%
This is it, the capital IT.

00:25:48.740 --> 00:25:49.530 align:middle line:90%
This is it.

00:25:49.530 --> 00:25:51.470 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing else.

00:25:51.470 --> 00:25:55.160 align:middle line:90%
As Ram Dass said, be here now.

00:25:55.160 --> 00:25:55.940 align:middle line:90%
It was true.

00:25:55.940 --> 00:25:57.230 align:middle line:90%
Be here now.

00:25:57.230 --> 00:25:58.840 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And the power of now.

00:25:58.840 --> 00:25:59.820 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Power of now.

00:25:59.820 --> 00:26:00.720 align:middle line:90%
Now is it.

00:26:00.720 --> 00:26:01.480 align:middle line:90%
Where it's at.

00:26:01.480 --> 00:26:02.200 align:middle line:90%
Now is it.

00:26:02.200 --> 00:26:03.350 align:middle line:90%
Now is gone now.

00:26:03.350 --> 00:26:04.512 align:middle line:90%
Now is a new now.

00:26:04.512 --> 00:26:05.262 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right now.

00:26:05.262 --> 00:26:05.761 align:middle line:90%
Yes, yes.

00:26:05.761 --> 00:26:06.390 align:middle line:90%
And now is now.

00:26:06.390 --> 00:26:06.890 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:26:06.890 --> 00:26:07.670 align:middle line:90%
This is a new now.

00:26:07.670 --> 00:26:09.120 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: It's a new now.

00:26:09.120 --> 00:26:11.730 align:middle line:84%
And this is time passing
in the human realm.

00:26:11.730 --> 00:26:14.130 align:middle line:84%
So you want to make the
most of every moment.

00:26:14.130 --> 00:26:17.444 align:middle line:84%
And you could squander it
worrying and being in fear,

00:26:17.444 --> 00:26:19.110 align:middle line:84%
but as we said, the
minute you get sick,

00:26:19.110 --> 00:26:20.130 align:middle line:90%
your energy is limited.

00:26:20.130 --> 00:26:21.860 align:middle line:84%
You don't have the
energy to worry anymore.

00:26:21.860 --> 00:26:23.820 align:middle line:84%
When you're feeling well,
you have all this energy.

00:26:23.820 --> 00:26:25.320 align:middle line:84%
And you can choose
how to use it.

00:26:25.320 --> 00:26:26.977 align:middle line:90%
You could waste it worrying.

00:26:26.977 --> 00:26:28.810 align:middle line:84%
Now, I talk about in
the book the difference

00:26:28.810 --> 00:26:30.680 align:middle line:90%
between concern and worry.

00:26:30.680 --> 00:26:33.740 align:middle line:84%
Now concern is just
having legitimate concerns

00:26:33.740 --> 00:26:34.700 align:middle line:90%
about something.

00:26:34.700 --> 00:26:37.410 align:middle line:84%
Worrying is a form of
rumination and suffering.

00:26:37.410 --> 00:26:38.910 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, because
it lasts longer,

00:26:38.910 --> 00:26:40.530 align:middle line:90%
and it's usually not founded.

00:26:40.530 --> 00:26:42.113 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Beat, beat,
beat over, over.

00:26:42.113 --> 00:26:43.730 align:middle line:90%
Rumination circles.

00:26:43.730 --> 00:26:45.620 align:middle line:84%
Being concerned, I'm
concerned about my child

00:26:45.620 --> 00:26:46.870 align:middle line:90%
because she doesn't feel well.

00:26:46.870 --> 00:26:48.510 align:middle line:90%
That's legitimate.

00:26:48.510 --> 00:26:50.374 align:middle line:84%
But I'm concerned
she's going to die.

00:26:50.374 --> 00:26:51.540 align:middle line:90%
She's not going to be there.

00:26:51.540 --> 00:26:53.790 align:middle line:90%
You know, around and around.

00:26:53.790 --> 00:26:56.830 align:middle line:84%
Part of surrender is
working things down instead

00:26:56.830 --> 00:26:59.189 align:middle line:84%
of the drama of
working things up.

00:26:59.189 --> 00:27:00.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What do you mean?

00:27:00.230 --> 00:27:01.396 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: You have a choice.

00:27:01.396 --> 00:27:05.360 align:middle line:84%
You can fuel fear, or
you can bring it down.

00:27:05.360 --> 00:27:06.950 align:middle line:90%
You can make things small.

00:27:06.950 --> 00:27:08.990 align:middle line:84%
I have a Taoist
spiritual teacher,

00:27:08.990 --> 00:27:10.420 align:middle line:90%
and he says make things small.

00:27:10.420 --> 00:27:11.730 align:middle line:90%
Don't make them large.

00:27:11.730 --> 00:27:12.800 align:middle line:90%
Don't blow them up.

00:27:12.800 --> 00:27:14.090 align:middle line:90%
Make them smaller.

00:27:14.090 --> 00:27:18.137 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So denominalizing
issues, drama, whatever it is?

00:27:18.137 --> 00:27:18.970 align:middle line:90%
Just taking it down.

00:27:18.970 --> 00:27:20.110 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Well, drama.

00:27:20.110 --> 00:27:22.550 align:middle line:84%
It's just like saying, I
have been through so much

00:27:22.550 --> 00:27:23.160 align:middle line:90%
in my life.

00:27:23.160 --> 00:27:24.202 align:middle line:90%
Here's another challenge.

00:27:24.202 --> 00:27:25.451 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to get through this.

00:27:25.451 --> 00:27:27.030 align:middle line:84%
At the moment, I
can't figure it out,

00:27:27.030 --> 00:27:30.530 align:middle line:84%
but we'll get through it
as opposed to oh my god,

00:27:30.530 --> 00:27:32.974 align:middle line:90%
my life is over.

00:27:32.974 --> 00:27:34.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:27:34.230 --> 00:27:35.980 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, I can tend
to get in the moment

00:27:35.980 --> 00:27:40.500 align:middle line:84%
so much that I do make
myself late a lot.

00:27:40.500 --> 00:27:42.290 align:middle line:90%
But then that causes anxiety.

00:27:42.290 --> 00:27:44.540 align:middle line:84%
So there's one thing about
surrendering in the moment,

00:27:44.540 --> 00:27:48.300 align:middle line:84%
but then you also have to
stay keen to your commitments.

00:27:48.300 --> 00:27:49.117 align:middle line:90%
How do you do that?

00:27:49.117 --> 00:27:50.200 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Well, it's both.

00:27:50.200 --> 00:27:52.210 align:middle line:84%
It's the reality of
time commitments.

00:27:52.210 --> 00:27:55.460 align:middle line:84%
You could set a timer on your
phone or something like that.

00:27:55.460 --> 00:27:57.930 align:middle line:84%
You have to because, otherwise,
you'll never get anywhere.

00:27:57.930 --> 00:27:58.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:27:58.390 --> 00:27:58.890 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:27:58.890 --> 00:28:00.140 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:28:00.140 --> 00:28:01.560 align:middle line:90%
And fulfill those commitments.

00:28:01.560 --> 00:28:02.059 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:28:02.059 --> 00:28:04.690 align:middle line:84%
We're going to take another
look at the Ted Talk

00:28:04.690 --> 00:28:06.330 align:middle line:90%
that Dr. Judith Orloff gave.

00:28:06.330 --> 00:28:08.660 align:middle line:84%
And in this particular place,
she's talking about one

00:28:08.660 --> 00:28:09.326 align:middle line:90%
of her patients.

00:28:09.326 --> 00:28:10.590 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:28:10.590 --> 00:28:13.920 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: I had a patient,
Eve, who was 92 years old.

00:28:13.920 --> 00:28:15.990 align:middle line:90%
And her daughter was dying.

00:28:15.990 --> 00:28:19.270 align:middle line:84%
When her daughter died, she
called me to be by her side

00:28:19.270 --> 00:28:21.390 align:middle line:90%
in the hospital at Cedar Sinai.

00:28:21.390 --> 00:28:23.520 align:middle line:84%
And as I was going
down the hall,

00:28:23.520 --> 00:28:25.857 align:middle line:84%
I heard her wailing
and screaming.

00:28:25.857 --> 00:28:28.106 align:middle line:84%
The nurses came up to me,
and they were very concerned

00:28:28.106 --> 00:28:29.630 align:middle line:84%
with her, that she
would collapse.

00:28:29.630 --> 00:28:32.720 align:middle line:84%
She was a little old
lady, very frail.

00:28:32.720 --> 00:28:36.070 align:middle line:84%
And she was really, really
making a lot of noise.

00:28:36.070 --> 00:28:39.450 align:middle line:84%
And in my psychiatric
training at USC and UCLA,

00:28:39.450 --> 00:28:42.590 align:middle line:84%
I was trained to treat
patients at a kind of distance

00:28:42.590 --> 00:28:44.640 align:middle line:84%
and certainly to
never touch them.

00:28:44.640 --> 00:28:47.200 align:middle line:84%
We were never trained
to even put a hand

00:28:47.200 --> 00:28:49.800 align:middle line:84%
or pat them on the back,
keep a safe distance.

00:28:49.800 --> 00:28:52.000 align:middle line:84%
But the minute I
walked into that room,

00:28:52.000 --> 00:28:55.550 align:middle line:84%
this little lady
jumped into my arms

00:28:55.550 --> 00:28:59.110 align:middle line:84%
and wrapped her body around
mine in the fetal position

00:28:59.110 --> 00:29:01.220 align:middle line:90%
and was wailing and crying.

00:29:01.220 --> 00:29:03.580 align:middle line:90%
And her tears were all over me.

00:29:03.580 --> 00:29:06.520 align:middle line:84%
And the newly minted
psychiatrist in me

00:29:06.520 --> 00:29:07.630 align:middle line:90%
was in total shock.

00:29:07.630 --> 00:29:10.920 align:middle line:84%
But I knew that I had to
surrender to that moment

00:29:10.920 --> 00:29:13.180 align:middle line:90%
because it's what Eve needed.

00:29:13.180 --> 00:29:16.170 align:middle line:84%
And it's what was
right, you see.

00:29:16.170 --> 00:29:19.520 align:middle line:84%
And so she spent
about an hour crying.

00:29:19.520 --> 00:29:23.270 align:middle line:84%
And then she detached
herself from me, basically.

00:29:23.270 --> 00:29:24.260 align:middle line:90%
And we talked.

00:29:24.260 --> 00:29:27.790 align:middle line:84%
And then that was the beginning
of her grieving process.

00:29:27.790 --> 00:29:32.720 align:middle line:84%
So I learned how important
it is to trust the moment,

00:29:32.720 --> 00:29:34.260 align:middle line:90%
to be there with people.

00:29:34.260 --> 00:29:37.200 align:middle line:84%
It might not be
what you thought.

00:29:37.200 --> 00:29:40.730 align:middle line:84%
It might not be what you
thought, but it is what it is.

00:29:40.730 --> 00:29:41.850 align:middle line:90%
So you flow with that.

00:29:41.850 --> 00:29:44.570 align:middle line:84%
And you trust the
integrity of that.

00:29:44.570 --> 00:29:47.750 align:middle line:90%
That's trusting life.

00:29:47.750 --> 00:29:49.300 align:middle line:84%
I'm so passionate
about surrender

00:29:49.300 --> 00:29:52.290 align:middle line:84%
because I learned about
it from my mother,

00:29:52.290 --> 00:29:54.200 align:middle line:84%
in terms of how she
didn't surrender.

00:29:54.200 --> 00:29:57.120 align:middle line:90%


00:29:57.120 --> 00:30:01.450 align:middle line:84%
At age 70, she was a family
practitioner in Beverly Hills,

00:30:01.450 --> 00:30:04.570 align:middle line:84%
and she decided to take
her national board exams.

00:30:04.570 --> 00:30:06.670 align:middle line:84%
And for those of you
who know what this is,

00:30:06.670 --> 00:30:09.890 align:middle line:84%
it's as intense as the
bar exam is for lawyers.

00:30:09.890 --> 00:30:10.790 align:middle line:90%
It's so intense.

00:30:10.790 --> 00:30:13.260 align:middle line:84%
And she felt that she
needed to do this in order

00:30:13.260 --> 00:30:15.890 align:middle line:84%
to keep up with the
younger doctors.

00:30:15.890 --> 00:30:20.380 align:middle line:84%
And at that point, she was about
the best healer I've ever met.

00:30:20.380 --> 00:30:22.780 align:middle line:90%
And she had a huge practice.

00:30:22.780 --> 00:30:25.290 align:middle line:84%
And she had all these
patients who loved her.

00:30:25.290 --> 00:30:26.900 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, when I
was a little girl,

00:30:26.900 --> 00:30:29.860 align:middle line:84%
I used to go on
house calls with her.

00:30:29.860 --> 00:30:31.890 align:middle line:84%
And she even took
me to the hospital

00:30:31.890 --> 00:30:34.280 align:middle line:84%
when she made chicken
soup for Mick Jagger

00:30:34.280 --> 00:30:37.350 align:middle line:90%
when I was a teenager.

00:30:37.350 --> 00:30:38.560 align:middle line:90%
So I got to meet him.

00:30:38.560 --> 00:30:40.940 align:middle line:84%
You can imagine what
a thrill that was.

00:30:40.940 --> 00:30:43.270 align:middle line:84%
I used to go with her
in her pink Cadillac

00:30:43.270 --> 00:30:46.790 align:middle line:90%
up into the hills of Bel Air.

00:30:46.790 --> 00:30:48.510 align:middle line:84%
And I would watch
her with patients.

00:30:48.510 --> 00:30:50.300 align:middle line:84%
She would listen
with a stethoscope.

00:30:50.300 --> 00:30:53.469 align:middle line:84%
She had a bag, the old
time family doctor.

00:30:53.469 --> 00:30:55.010 align:middle line:84%
And she would listen
to her patients.

00:30:55.010 --> 00:30:57.730 align:middle line:90%
She was truly so gifted.

00:30:57.730 --> 00:31:01.720 align:middle line:84%
But the thing about my mother
was that a million people could

00:31:01.720 --> 00:31:05.110 align:middle line:84%
tell her how wonderful she
was, and she would only

00:31:05.110 --> 00:31:08.100 align:middle line:84%
look at her negative
points and her self-doubt.

00:31:08.100 --> 00:31:10.560 align:middle line:84%
And that's not unlike
a lot of people

00:31:10.560 --> 00:31:12.400 align:middle line:84%
that you could have
so much going for you,

00:31:12.400 --> 00:31:15.650 align:middle line:84%
but yet a small percentage--
somebody says one little thing,

00:31:15.650 --> 00:31:17.130 align:middle line:90%
and you're off and running.

00:31:17.130 --> 00:31:19.890 align:middle line:84%
And so she took this
exam and put herself

00:31:19.890 --> 00:31:22.110 align:middle line:90%
through so much stress.

00:31:22.110 --> 00:31:23.960 align:middle line:84%
And 20 years before
that, she had

00:31:23.960 --> 00:31:28.270 align:middle line:84%
been diagnosed with a
pretty benign lymphoma.

00:31:28.270 --> 00:31:30.180 align:middle line:84%
But while she was
taking the test,

00:31:30.180 --> 00:31:33.260 align:middle line:84%
the months she took studying,
and beating herself up,

00:31:33.260 --> 00:31:36.610 align:middle line:84%
and not feeling she was
enough, the cell type

00:31:36.610 --> 00:31:40.590 align:middle line:90%
changed to a malignant leukemia.

00:31:40.590 --> 00:31:42.880 align:middle line:84%
And although my
mother heroically

00:31:42.880 --> 00:31:48.160 align:middle line:84%
passed the test,
soon after, she died.

00:31:48.160 --> 00:31:50.650 align:middle line:84%
And as she was
dying, she said to me

00:31:50.650 --> 00:31:53.320 align:middle line:84%
that she felt the
stress of the test

00:31:53.320 --> 00:31:56.710 align:middle line:84%
was what caused the
cell type to change.

00:31:56.710 --> 00:32:01.020 align:middle line:84%
And so as her daughter, I was
really standing there helpless.

00:32:01.020 --> 00:32:03.080 align:middle line:84%
There was nothing I
could do to intervene.

00:32:03.080 --> 00:32:05.020 align:middle line:90%
I was there supporting her.

00:32:05.020 --> 00:32:07.280 align:middle line:90%
But I watched my mother do this.

00:32:07.280 --> 00:32:11.020 align:middle line:84%
And it was through losing
the dearest person to me

00:32:11.020 --> 00:32:15.780 align:middle line:84%
that I gained a very hard lesson
on surrender, because I, too,

00:32:15.780 --> 00:32:17.260 align:middle line:90%
am a workaholic.

00:32:17.260 --> 00:32:19.350 align:middle line:90%
I, too, have self doubts.

00:32:19.350 --> 00:32:21.070 align:middle line:90%
I can push myself.

00:32:21.070 --> 00:32:22.860 align:middle line:90%
So I am my mother's daughter.

00:32:22.860 --> 00:32:27.620 align:middle line:84%
And so I knew in order for
me to be happy and free

00:32:27.620 --> 00:32:31.600 align:middle line:84%
and lead a beautiful life,
I needed to surrender.

00:32:31.600 --> 00:32:33.670 align:middle line:84%
I needed to learn
how to do that.

00:32:33.670 --> 00:32:37.890 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't want to follow in
her footsteps in that sense.

00:32:37.890 --> 00:32:42.190 align:middle line:84%
And so I learned early on what
it was like not to surrender

00:32:42.190 --> 00:32:43.670 align:middle line:84%
and that, you know,
sometimes life

00:32:43.670 --> 00:32:45.510 align:middle line:90%
gives you some hard lessons.

00:32:45.510 --> 00:32:48.240 align:middle line:84%
And I hope you all
learn from them.

00:32:48.240 --> 00:32:49.380 align:middle line:90%
We all have hard lessons.

00:32:49.380 --> 00:32:50.730 align:middle line:90%
I hope you learn from them.

00:32:50.730 --> 00:32:53.470 align:middle line:84%
And I learned from
this, and thus, it

00:32:53.470 --> 00:32:57.920 align:middle line:84%
has spurred my passion in
what it means to surrender.

00:32:57.920 --> 00:33:00.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So we've talked
about being a control freak.

00:33:00.540 --> 00:33:04.540 align:middle line:84%
And it's such a weird
word to give it, freak.

00:33:04.540 --> 00:33:06.990 align:middle line:84%
Is there a good side
to being controlling?

00:33:06.990 --> 00:33:10.360 align:middle line:84%
Is there a shadow side
to it and a positive sign

00:33:10.360 --> 00:33:12.050 align:middle line:90%
to being controlling at all?

00:33:12.050 --> 00:33:13.050 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Oh absolutely.

00:33:13.050 --> 00:33:15.258 align:middle line:84%
I mean in some situations,
you want to be in control.

00:33:15.258 --> 00:33:17.410 align:middle line:84%
When you're a parent, you
need to be in control.

00:33:17.410 --> 00:33:18.790 align:middle line:84%
You can't let your
child run you.

00:33:18.790 --> 00:33:21.090 align:middle line:84%
You have to be the
one who's in control.

00:33:21.090 --> 00:33:24.090 align:middle line:84%
If you're leading a business,
you have to be a leader.

00:33:24.090 --> 00:33:26.570 align:middle line:84%
You have to be in control
at the same time yielding

00:33:26.570 --> 00:33:27.480 align:middle line:90%
to other people.

00:33:27.480 --> 00:33:28.770 align:middle line:90%
It's balance.

00:33:28.770 --> 00:33:31.680 align:middle line:84%
A control freak never
lets anybody do anything.

00:33:31.680 --> 00:33:33.140 align:middle line:90%
They never delegate.

00:33:33.140 --> 00:33:34.770 align:middle line:84%
They want to do
everything themselves.

00:33:34.770 --> 00:33:36.180 align:middle line:90%
And you can't do it right.

00:33:36.180 --> 00:33:37.870 align:middle line:84%
And that's not a way
to run a business,

00:33:37.870 --> 00:33:40.560 align:middle line:84%
or a corporation, or
anything because people

00:33:40.560 --> 00:33:41.810 align:middle line:90%
want to feel valued.

00:33:41.810 --> 00:33:44.774 align:middle line:84%
And if you're not allowing
people to do their creativity,

00:33:44.774 --> 00:33:46.440 align:middle line:84%
and you're trying to
control everything,

00:33:46.440 --> 00:33:48.500 align:middle line:90%
you're stifling them.

00:33:48.500 --> 00:33:52.250 align:middle line:84%
But it's good to control
certain things in terms of you

00:33:52.250 --> 00:33:53.190 align:middle line:90%
want to go to college.

00:33:53.190 --> 00:33:54.170 align:middle line:90%
You want to study.

00:33:54.170 --> 00:33:57.480 align:middle line:84%
I had to control a lot going
through medical school,

00:33:57.480 --> 00:33:59.390 align:middle line:90%
my psychiatric residency.

00:33:59.390 --> 00:34:01.840 align:middle line:84%
I had to really control
my mind and study,

00:34:01.840 --> 00:34:05.330 align:middle line:84%
study, study all the time
and get a lot of sleep.

00:34:05.330 --> 00:34:07.850 align:middle line:84%
And when I worked with
patients, and I was on call

00:34:07.850 --> 00:34:10.690 align:middle line:84%
every third night
for many, many years.

00:34:10.690 --> 00:34:13.800 align:middle line:84%
You really are in control
in those situations.

00:34:13.800 --> 00:34:16.670 align:middle line:84%
Patients come to you in
life and death emergencies.

00:34:16.670 --> 00:34:18.659 align:middle line:84%
So it's good for
me to be in control

00:34:18.659 --> 00:34:20.589 align:middle line:84%
and know what to do and
know what to prescribe

00:34:20.589 --> 00:34:22.280 align:middle line:90%
or what tests to order.

00:34:22.280 --> 00:34:23.047 align:middle line:90%
I had to be.

00:34:23.047 --> 00:34:23.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:34:23.880 --> 00:34:24.860 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:34:24.860 --> 00:34:28.860 align:middle line:84%
And being as empathic
and intuitive as you are,

00:34:28.860 --> 00:34:31.040 align:middle line:84%
was that challenging
for you, where

00:34:31.040 --> 00:34:34.210 align:middle line:84%
you would see people come
with mental illness or demons

00:34:34.210 --> 00:34:35.050 align:middle line:90%
or things like that.

00:34:35.050 --> 00:34:39.810 align:middle line:84%
Was it hard for you to
monitor your intuition

00:34:39.810 --> 00:34:40.942 align:middle line:90%
during those times?

00:34:40.942 --> 00:34:42.900 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Well, you know,
it was so interesting

00:34:42.900 --> 00:34:44.880 align:middle line:84%
because in those
times of crisis,

00:34:44.880 --> 00:34:48.230 align:middle line:84%
I'm out of my personal self,
and I'm into a selfless mode.

00:34:48.230 --> 00:34:50.739 align:middle line:84%
And so when I'm not
in my personal self,

00:34:50.739 --> 00:34:54.429 align:middle line:84%
I don't get drained as much
until afterwards just sheer

00:34:54.429 --> 00:34:55.810 align:middle line:90%
not sleeping.

00:34:55.810 --> 00:34:59.020 align:middle line:84%
But when somebody is in front
of me with an emergency,

00:34:59.020 --> 00:35:01.100 align:middle line:84%
I go out of my personal
self, and I just

00:35:01.100 --> 00:35:03.830 align:middle line:84%
click into intuitive
knowing, quick, fast.

00:35:03.830 --> 00:35:06.130 align:middle line:84%
I mean that's the
advantage of my being

00:35:06.130 --> 00:35:08.660 align:middle line:84%
an intuitive psychiatrist is
that somebody can come to me,

00:35:08.660 --> 00:35:09.870 align:middle line:90%
and I bam, bam, bam.

00:35:09.870 --> 00:35:14.050 align:middle line:84%
I get pretty much
the story quickly.

00:35:14.050 --> 00:35:16.117 align:middle line:84%
I don't wait weeks and
weeks to figure it out.

00:35:16.117 --> 00:35:16.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:35:16.700 --> 00:35:20.750 align:middle line:84%
So you can intuit that and then
help somebody faster, and not

00:35:20.750 --> 00:35:22.320 align:middle line:90%
prolong a problem.

00:35:22.320 --> 00:35:23.861 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: The misery.

00:35:23.861 --> 00:35:24.360 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

