00:35:46.820 --> 00:35:52.690 align:middle line:84%
So how can you surrender in a--
it says letting go of power.

00:35:52.690 --> 00:35:54.800 align:middle line:90%
Letting go of power.

00:35:54.800 --> 00:35:57.270 align:middle line:84%
So when you surrender
in that place,

00:35:57.270 --> 00:35:59.950 align:middle line:84%
how do you surrender and
be in a place of power

00:35:59.950 --> 00:36:00.660 align:middle line:90%
at the same time?

00:36:00.660 --> 00:36:01.732 align:middle line:90%
You can't, can you?

00:36:01.732 --> 00:36:03.940 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Well, what I'm
talking about-- in the book,

00:36:03.940 --> 00:36:05.314 align:middle line:84%
I go through
different surrenders

00:36:05.314 --> 00:36:06.310 align:middle line:90%
in different chapters.

00:36:06.310 --> 00:36:09.110 align:middle line:84%
And one is surrender your
old views about power.

00:36:09.110 --> 00:36:13.020 align:middle line:84%
And what I mean by that is the
egocentric view and the greed

00:36:13.020 --> 00:36:16.510 align:middle line:84%
view of power, or I need
to control everybody,

00:36:16.510 --> 00:36:21.930 align:middle line:84%
the corporate view, the
old paradigm view of power.

00:36:21.930 --> 00:36:24.040 align:middle line:84%
And what I'm suggesting
is to surrender that

00:36:24.040 --> 00:36:27.630 align:middle line:84%
and to come into a more heart
centered view of power, which

00:36:27.630 --> 00:36:30.840 align:middle line:84%
is really more the
soft forms of power

00:36:30.840 --> 00:36:32.970 align:middle line:84%
versus the hard
forms of power, which

00:36:32.970 --> 00:36:37.530 align:middle line:84%
are adrenaline and
testosterone ruling the world.

00:36:37.530 --> 00:36:39.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So what is
another view of power?

00:36:39.770 --> 00:36:42.770 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Another view of
power is to look at true power.

00:36:42.770 --> 00:36:45.250 align:middle line:84%
What makes a truly
powerful person?

00:36:45.250 --> 00:36:47.400 align:middle line:84%
Is it the amount
of money they have?

00:36:47.400 --> 00:36:50.790 align:middle line:84%
Is it whatever they
have on the outside?

00:36:50.790 --> 00:36:54.400 align:middle line:84%
Yes, in terms of worldly power,
but if you equate happiness

00:36:54.400 --> 00:36:56.850 align:middle line:84%
with power, it's a bit
of a different thing.

00:36:56.850 --> 00:36:57.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And love.

00:36:57.590 --> 00:36:59.720 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: And love,
and heart centered,

00:36:59.720 --> 00:37:02.160 align:middle line:84%
and giving back to
the world, and being

00:37:02.160 --> 00:37:05.090 align:middle line:84%
conscious of the
Earth, and being

00:37:05.090 --> 00:37:08.160 align:middle line:84%
devoted to your inner
work and your inner life.

00:37:08.160 --> 00:37:10.020 align:middle line:90%
That makes people happy.

00:37:10.020 --> 00:37:12.730 align:middle line:84%
I talk about in the book
the happiness set point.

00:37:12.730 --> 00:37:16.550 align:middle line:84%
That's the basic level of
happiness we feel in our lives.

00:37:16.550 --> 00:37:18.910 align:middle line:84%
And it's been proven that
if you win the lottery,

00:37:18.910 --> 00:37:21.260 align:middle line:84%
you'll get happier for
a little period of time,

00:37:21.260 --> 00:37:24.510 align:middle line:84%
but you'll go back to your same
level of misery you had before.

00:37:24.510 --> 00:37:26.410 align:middle line:84%
But what will change
the happiness set

00:37:26.410 --> 00:37:29.970 align:middle line:84%
point is if you meditate,
if you come from your heart,

00:37:29.970 --> 00:37:32.820 align:middle line:84%
if you do good,
if you surrender,

00:37:32.820 --> 00:37:34.530 align:middle line:90%
then you get happier.

00:37:34.530 --> 00:37:37.990 align:middle line:84%
The happiness set point changes,
and you're happier more often.

00:37:37.990 --> 00:37:40.750 align:middle line:90%
And to me, that's the goal.

00:37:40.750 --> 00:37:43.920 align:middle line:84%
Why be king of the world
if you're not happy?

00:37:43.920 --> 00:37:46.339 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's happened
too many times.

00:37:46.339 --> 00:37:47.630 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: But what's the point?

00:37:47.630 --> 00:37:51.280 align:middle line:84%
I've worked with so many people,
corporate executives, studio

00:37:51.280 --> 00:37:53.220 align:middle line:84%
heads who've had
these huge jobs.

00:37:53.220 --> 00:37:55.980 align:middle line:84%
And then they age,
and the job is gone.

00:37:55.980 --> 00:38:01.390 align:middle line:84%
And they wonder why their wives
don't have passion for them

00:38:01.390 --> 00:38:03.090 align:middle line:90%
or where their friends are.

00:38:03.090 --> 00:38:06.840 align:middle line:84%
And so at any point, people
could start a spiritual path,

00:38:06.840 --> 00:38:07.840 align:middle line:90%
at any point.

00:38:07.840 --> 00:38:11.480 align:middle line:90%
It's just harder when you're 70.

00:38:11.480 --> 00:38:11.980 align:middle line:90%
You can.

00:38:11.980 --> 00:38:14.240 align:middle line:90%
But any age, it's possible.

00:38:14.240 --> 00:38:17.950 align:middle line:84%
And I support people at any age
beginning their spiritual path.

00:38:17.950 --> 00:38:20.150 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you also talk
about redefining success

00:38:20.150 --> 00:38:23.320 align:middle line:84%
along these same
lines of surrendering

00:38:23.320 --> 00:38:25.030 align:middle line:90%
to a new definition of success.

00:38:25.030 --> 00:38:27.350 align:middle line:84%
Take, for example,
retiring and moving

00:38:27.350 --> 00:38:29.980 align:middle line:90%
into a different level of life.

00:38:29.980 --> 00:38:33.090 align:middle line:84%
How do you suggest
to someone retiring

00:38:33.090 --> 00:38:35.620 align:middle line:90%
to a new definition of success?

00:38:35.620 --> 00:38:38.170 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Well, success is
your level of happiness.

00:38:38.170 --> 00:38:41.140 align:middle line:84%
And your level of fulfillment
and connection with yourself

00:38:41.140 --> 00:38:42.750 align:middle line:90%
is the inner surrender.

00:38:42.750 --> 00:38:45.480 align:middle line:84%
It's surrendering to
what's inside of you.

00:38:45.480 --> 00:38:47.770 align:middle line:84%
So much of part of
the spiritual path

00:38:47.770 --> 00:38:50.310 align:middle line:84%
is about going inside,
feeling yourself,

00:38:50.310 --> 00:38:53.120 align:middle line:84%
and not fighting yourself,
feeling your soul

00:38:53.120 --> 00:38:54.910 align:middle line:84%
and surrendering to
your soul's mission,

00:38:54.910 --> 00:38:59.000 align:middle line:84%
whether it's retiring or running
a corporation or being in love

00:38:59.000 --> 00:39:02.430 align:middle line:84%
or not being in love or
whatever you're doing,

00:39:02.430 --> 00:39:04.950 align:middle line:90%
surrender to your inner self.

00:39:04.950 --> 00:39:07.270 align:middle line:84%
Surrender to you
because that's who

00:39:07.270 --> 00:39:11.170 align:middle line:84%
goes with you when you
leave this wherever.

00:39:11.170 --> 00:39:12.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:39:12.670 --> 00:39:14.470 align:middle line:84%
All right, let's talk
about relationships.

00:39:14.470 --> 00:39:20.540 align:middle line:84%
Surrendering to the-- you
mention obsessive relationships

00:39:20.540 --> 00:39:23.480 align:middle line:84%
where people are
unavailable emotionally.

00:39:23.480 --> 00:39:26.290 align:middle line:84%
Not surrendering to those
but surrendering to-- yeah,

00:39:26.290 --> 00:39:28.710 align:middle line:84%
I caught myself
there-- surrendering

00:39:28.710 --> 00:39:31.470 align:middle line:84%
to no longer being in
those relationships.

00:39:31.470 --> 00:39:32.262 align:middle line:90%
How do you do that?

00:39:32.262 --> 00:39:33.886 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: There's a
chapter in the book

00:39:33.886 --> 00:39:36.340 align:middle line:84%
on surrendering to soul
mates, and finding soul mates,

00:39:36.340 --> 00:39:38.160 align:middle line:84%
and finding healthy
relationships.

00:39:38.160 --> 00:39:41.310 align:middle line:84%
And part of that-- and so many
patients come to me saying I

00:39:41.310 --> 00:39:43.280 align:middle line:90%
want my soul mate.

00:39:43.280 --> 00:39:45.210 align:middle line:84%
But there's no
good men out there.

00:39:45.210 --> 00:39:47.330 align:middle line:84%
There's no good women
out there, whatever

00:39:47.330 --> 00:39:51.730 align:middle line:84%
that is, that statement is and
that mass belief that that's

00:39:51.730 --> 00:39:52.870 align:middle line:90%
true.

00:39:52.870 --> 00:39:55.380 align:middle line:84%
And my work with
them and in the book,

00:39:55.380 --> 00:39:58.220 align:middle line:84%
how to surrender patterns
that keep you from love.

00:39:58.220 --> 00:40:00.990 align:middle line:84%
And one of the patterns
is being attracted

00:40:00.990 --> 00:40:03.400 align:middle line:90%
to unavailable men or women.

00:40:03.400 --> 00:40:04.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Big pattern.

00:40:04.780 --> 00:40:06.260 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Big pattern.

00:40:06.260 --> 00:40:07.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Popular pattern.

00:40:07.500 --> 00:40:08.790 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Popular pattern.

00:40:08.790 --> 00:40:09.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What does
that stem from?

00:40:09.040 --> 00:40:10.650 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: It usually
stems from having

00:40:10.650 --> 00:40:12.970 align:middle line:84%
a father who wasn't
available or a mother who

00:40:12.970 --> 00:40:16.390 align:middle line:84%
was too suffocating, so you
wanted to get away from her.

00:40:16.390 --> 00:40:18.040 align:middle line:84%
So when someone
gets close to you,

00:40:18.040 --> 00:40:21.850 align:middle line:84%
you start freaking out because
there's too much closeness,

00:40:21.850 --> 00:40:23.900 align:middle line:84%
and you associate
it with suffocation.

00:40:23.900 --> 00:40:26.560 align:middle line:84%
So part of the work
is realizing you

00:40:26.560 --> 00:40:30.807 align:middle line:84%
can't find a mate who's
unavailable, transform them,

00:40:30.807 --> 00:40:33.390 align:middle line:84%
and that will heal your initial
relationship with your father.

00:40:33.390 --> 00:40:36.280 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't work, though
people try it all the time.

00:40:36.280 --> 00:40:38.190 align:middle line:84%
They think if only--
I found this guy.

00:40:38.190 --> 00:40:39.420 align:middle line:90%
He's not available.

00:40:39.420 --> 00:40:42.610 align:middle line:84%
But if only I could change him,
I could get him to love me,

00:40:42.610 --> 00:40:45.380 align:middle line:84%
then somehow the inner
psyche thinks, oh, then

00:40:45.380 --> 00:40:48.480 align:middle line:84%
I'll heal the pattern
from my father.

00:40:48.480 --> 00:40:51.200 align:middle line:84%
And as much as that may
make sense to people,

00:40:51.200 --> 00:40:51.876 align:middle line:90%
it never works.

00:40:51.876 --> 00:40:54.500 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you think that's why
there are so many affairs where

00:40:54.500 --> 00:40:56.860 align:middle line:84%
women go after unavailable
men that are married

00:40:56.860 --> 00:40:59.900 align:middle line:84%
or men go after unavailable
women who are married.

00:40:59.900 --> 00:41:02.880 align:middle line:84%
Do you think this
stems from that?

00:41:02.880 --> 00:41:05.520 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Well, maybe if
they're looking for connection

00:41:05.520 --> 00:41:07.370 align:middle line:90%
with that person.

00:41:07.370 --> 00:41:10.700 align:middle line:84%
Yes, but I think so many
people are commitment phobic

00:41:10.700 --> 00:41:13.100 align:middle line:84%
because of what's
happened to them early on.

00:41:13.100 --> 00:41:14.850 align:middle line:90%
They're afraid of suffocation.

00:41:14.850 --> 00:41:16.950 align:middle line:84%
And in the book, I
talk about empaths.

00:41:16.950 --> 00:41:20.250 align:middle line:84%
And empaths are people who
are very open and sensitive,

00:41:20.250 --> 00:41:24.680 align:middle line:84%
like emotional sponges, but they
take on the stress of others.

00:41:24.680 --> 00:41:27.850 align:middle line:84%
So I talk about what is
a relationship empath.

00:41:27.850 --> 00:41:29.570 align:middle line:84%
And a relationship
empath is somebody

00:41:29.570 --> 00:41:31.910 align:middle line:84%
who takes on the
stress of their spouse,

00:41:31.910 --> 00:41:36.040 align:middle line:84%
so then they avoid relationships
because they feel engulfed

00:41:36.040 --> 00:41:38.330 align:middle line:84%
by being too close
in relationships.

00:41:38.330 --> 00:41:40.830 align:middle line:84%
And so for empaths--
and I'm an empath--

00:41:40.830 --> 00:41:43.340 align:middle line:84%
I always have to negotiate
my square footage needs

00:41:43.340 --> 00:41:46.390 align:middle line:84%
with people so they're not
on top of me all the time.

00:41:46.390 --> 00:41:47.664 align:middle line:90%
And it's a balance.

00:41:47.664 --> 00:41:48.580 align:middle line:90%
It's really a balance.

00:41:48.580 --> 00:41:49.955 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well
because you probably

00:41:49.955 --> 00:41:53.180 align:middle line:84%
feel into them so much more than
if they just give you an inch,

00:41:53.180 --> 00:41:54.596 align:middle line:90%
you see the mile.

00:41:54.596 --> 00:41:55.370 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Yeah.

00:41:55.370 --> 00:41:56.027 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, yeah.

00:41:56.027 --> 00:41:56.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:41:56.860 --> 00:41:58.990 align:middle line:84%
All right, so another
one is-- let's talk

00:41:58.990 --> 00:42:01.460 align:middle line:84%
about surrendering
to sexual power.

