If everyone listening here
just lets go, take a breath,

00:44:18.080 --> 00:44:21.350 align:middle line:90%
drink your water very slowly.

00:44:21.350 --> 00:44:24.330 align:middle line:84%
Just sit and feel
pleasure in your body.

00:44:24.330 --> 00:44:27.800 align:middle line:84%
Then the endorphins wake up and
start going through your body.

00:44:27.800 --> 00:44:29.350 align:middle line:84%
And that's-- notice
how you feel.

00:44:29.350 --> 00:44:31.750 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Created a domino
effect in the body.

00:44:31.750 --> 00:44:32.840 align:middle line:90%
That's beautiful.

00:44:32.840 --> 00:44:33.660 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: And that's
what you want.

00:44:33.660 --> 00:44:35.830 align:middle line:84%
But people don't realize
they're in charge of that.

00:44:35.830 --> 00:44:40.150 align:middle line:84%
And you could practice by being
in fear, just practice being

00:44:40.150 --> 00:44:40.650 align:middle line:90%
in fear.

00:44:40.650 --> 00:44:42.530 align:middle line:84%
Just get all your
fearful thoughts up,

00:44:42.530 --> 00:44:43.822 align:middle line:90%
see how you feel with all that.

00:44:43.822 --> 00:44:44.613 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Contracted.

00:44:44.613 --> 00:44:46.220 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Yes,
contracted, tense.

00:44:46.220 --> 00:44:49.000 align:middle line:84%
You could work yourself up, or
you can do it the other way.

00:44:49.000 --> 00:44:50.190 align:middle line:90%
And it's your choice.

00:44:50.190 --> 00:44:52.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Are there
other techniques

00:44:52.140 --> 00:44:54.520 align:middle line:84%
that you mention like
drinking the water slowly

00:44:54.520 --> 00:44:57.680 align:middle line:84%
that can instigate somebody
going into surrender that

00:44:57.680 --> 00:45:00.960 align:middle line:84%
could-- little, teeny things
that could really start someone

00:45:00.960 --> 00:45:03.880 align:middle line:84%
from unlocking themselves
from control to surrender?

00:45:03.880 --> 00:45:06.010 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Yes, just the
breath for one thing.

00:45:06.010 --> 00:45:08.220 align:middle line:90%
Just exhale, everyone listening.

00:45:08.220 --> 00:45:11.390 align:middle line:90%
Instead of clenching, just ah.

00:45:11.390 --> 00:45:13.970 align:middle line:84%
And you feel your
abdominal muscles release.

00:45:13.970 --> 00:45:15.460 align:middle line:90%
You feel energy going.

00:45:15.460 --> 00:45:18.060 align:middle line:90%
And your whole body, just relax.

00:45:18.060 --> 00:45:19.750 align:middle line:84%
And also put your
hand on your heart,

00:45:19.750 --> 00:45:22.400 align:middle line:84%
which is the heart
chakra, right here.

00:45:22.400 --> 00:45:25.680 align:middle line:84%
And begin to picture something
very loving or beautiful

00:45:25.680 --> 00:45:30.470 align:middle line:84%
such as the waterfall or
beautiful feathers or dancing.

00:45:30.470 --> 00:45:31.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Laughter.

00:45:31.680 --> 00:45:33.430 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Laughter.

00:45:33.430 --> 00:45:35.130 align:middle line:90%
And just get that pumping.

00:45:35.130 --> 00:45:37.510 align:middle line:84%
Get that energy pumping
from your heart.

00:45:37.510 --> 00:45:38.804 align:middle line:90%
You can move your energy.

00:45:38.804 --> 00:45:40.470 align:middle line:84%
And I work with all
my patients this way

00:45:40.470 --> 00:45:43.970 align:middle line:84%
to teach them how to move the
heart energy because if you're

00:45:43.970 --> 00:45:45.910 align:middle line:84%
having an anxiety attack
or you're starting

00:45:45.910 --> 00:45:48.320 align:middle line:84%
to get stressed, you have
to bring it down quickly.

00:45:48.320 --> 00:45:49.895 align:middle line:90%
And this is the soothing energy.

00:45:49.895 --> 00:45:51.830 align:middle line:84%
It's the healing
energy in the heart.

00:45:51.830 --> 00:45:53.740 align:middle line:84%
And the more you
become used to that,

00:45:53.740 --> 00:45:56.070 align:middle line:90%
the more you can surrender.

00:45:56.070 --> 00:45:58.530 align:middle line:90%
Or just take a big stretch.

00:45:58.530 --> 00:46:01.040 align:middle line:84%
One thing I suggest is
have everyone look up.

00:46:01.040 --> 00:46:02.280 align:middle line:90%
Look at the sky.

00:46:02.280 --> 00:46:06.070 align:middle line:84%
Notice your place
in the universe.

00:46:06.070 --> 00:46:08.510 align:middle line:84%
You'll be filled
with awe and wonder.

00:46:08.510 --> 00:46:12.554 align:middle line:84%
That's the point of surrender
is to get in touch with that.

00:46:12.554 --> 00:46:13.470 align:middle line:90%
And then let go to it.

00:46:13.470 --> 00:46:14.340 align:middle line:90%
Just look up.

00:46:14.340 --> 00:46:17.160 align:middle line:84%
Don't keep looking
horizontal or down.

00:46:17.160 --> 00:46:20.220 align:middle line:84%
In the night sky with
the various eclipses

00:46:20.220 --> 00:46:22.870 align:middle line:84%
we've been having, the blood
moon you know, just stay up

00:46:22.870 --> 00:46:23.490 align:middle line:90%
and watch it.

00:46:23.490 --> 00:46:23.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:46:23.990 --> 00:46:24.610 align:middle line:90%
Those are fun.

00:46:24.610 --> 00:46:26.610 align:middle line:90%
Yes, we did that.

00:46:26.610 --> 00:46:29.060 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about
surrendering to aging.

00:46:29.060 --> 00:46:32.295 align:middle line:84%
That's a part of the
twelve ways of letting go.

00:46:32.295 --> 00:46:34.610 align:middle line:84%
How can you-- how
do you surrender

00:46:34.610 --> 00:46:37.130 align:middle line:90%
to that aging process?

00:46:37.130 --> 00:46:40.070 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Yeah,
that's hard, isn't it?

00:46:40.070 --> 00:46:41.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Things
change in the body,

00:46:41.700 --> 00:46:44.420 align:middle line:90%
and things start to shrivel up.

00:46:44.420 --> 00:46:47.310 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Yeah, and then
you leave your body.

00:46:47.310 --> 00:46:49.940 align:middle line:84%
But leaving the body is
different than aging.

00:46:49.940 --> 00:46:53.070 align:middle line:84%
But Ram Dass talks about
that, a beautiful way

00:46:53.070 --> 00:46:55.420 align:middle line:84%
of talking about surrendering
during aging where you see

00:46:55.420 --> 00:47:00.150 align:middle line:84%
yourself more as a soul than an
ego, when you begin to identify

00:47:00.150 --> 00:47:02.300 align:middle line:84%
with your true
essence and your soul.

00:47:02.300 --> 00:47:05.410 align:middle line:90%
And you feel that primarily.

00:47:05.410 --> 00:47:08.810 align:middle line:84%
In the book, I talk
about spiritual aging.

00:47:08.810 --> 00:47:11.680 align:middle line:84%
And it's the only-- it
gets better with age.

00:47:11.680 --> 00:47:14.280 align:middle line:84%
The more you are devoted
to your spiritual path,

00:47:14.280 --> 00:47:17.340 align:middle line:84%
the more you connect, the older
you get, the better it gets.

00:47:17.340 --> 00:47:19.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The wiser
you get, absolutely.

00:47:19.040 --> 00:47:21.600 align:middle line:84%
But is there a difference
between being wiser

00:47:21.600 --> 00:47:23.580 align:middle line:90%
and surrendering?

00:47:23.580 --> 00:47:25.290 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Not necessarily wiser.

00:47:25.290 --> 00:47:29.270 align:middle line:84%
It is wiser, but it's more
connected to the mysteries

00:47:29.270 --> 00:47:32.810 align:middle line:84%
of the universe and to
your soul and to spirit.

00:47:32.810 --> 00:47:36.590 align:middle line:84%
And the more you can feel
that radiance of spirit

00:47:36.590 --> 00:47:39.760 align:middle line:90%
as you develop energetically.

00:47:39.760 --> 00:47:41.430 align:middle line:90%
Physical aging is one thing.

00:47:41.430 --> 00:47:43.770 align:middle line:84%
And there's certainly
a number of things

00:47:43.770 --> 00:47:45.790 align:middle line:84%
you can do to help
with physical aging.

00:47:45.790 --> 00:47:49.030 align:middle line:84%
And I go through everything
from bioidentical hormones

00:47:49.030 --> 00:47:51.410 align:middle line:84%
to supplements and other
things that can really

00:47:51.410 --> 00:47:54.030 align:middle line:84%
help physical
aging-- and exercise.

00:47:54.030 --> 00:47:55.620 align:middle line:84%
There are very
conscious things you

00:47:55.620 --> 00:47:58.550 align:middle line:84%
can do so you could be
as youthful as possible

00:47:58.550 --> 00:48:01.370 align:middle line:84%
and feel as good as possible
on the physical level.

00:48:01.370 --> 00:48:04.580 align:middle line:84%
But there's also spiritual
aging and surrendering

00:48:04.580 --> 00:48:08.080 align:middle line:84%
to the power that comes
from that, and the radiance

00:48:08.080 --> 00:48:10.520 align:middle line:84%
and the connection
with the universe.

00:48:10.520 --> 00:48:15.260 align:middle line:84%
Aging is about expanded
connections and development.

00:48:15.260 --> 00:48:17.530 align:middle line:90%
And then also emotional aging.

00:48:17.530 --> 00:48:19.680 align:middle line:90%
You could age well or not well.

00:48:19.680 --> 00:48:23.280 align:middle line:84%
And surrendering to, let's
say, letting go of fear.

00:48:23.280 --> 00:48:26.025 align:middle line:84%
And then as you age, fear
becomes less and less.

00:48:26.025 --> 00:48:26.900 align:middle line:90%
I mean, imagine that.

00:48:26.900 --> 00:48:27.816 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah, it does.

00:48:27.816 --> 00:48:30.900 align:middle line:84%
It denominalizes as you go
along because you realize

00:48:30.900 --> 00:48:33.165 align:middle line:84%
those things that you were
afraid of haven't happened

00:48:33.165 --> 00:48:34.030 align:middle line:90%
to this point.

00:48:34.030 --> 00:48:36.180 align:middle line:90%
And if they do, oh well.

00:48:36.180 --> 00:48:38.180 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: I just want to
say, I'm so much better

00:48:38.180 --> 00:48:40.700 align:middle line:84%
now at this age than
I was 20 years ago.

00:48:40.700 --> 00:48:43.190 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh yeah, we all are.

00:48:43.190 --> 00:48:43.690 align:middle line:90%
Age.

00:48:43.690 --> 00:48:47.160 align:middle line:84%
It does make us
wiser, but also you

00:48:47.160 --> 00:48:49.840 align:middle line:84%
don't care as much about
the little teeny things.

00:48:49.840 --> 00:48:53.750 align:middle line:84%
You realize that moment will
pass and that moment will pass.

00:48:53.750 --> 00:48:55.274 align:middle line:90%
And it just does.

00:48:55.274 --> 00:48:56.690 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: And you
go towards love.

00:48:56.690 --> 00:48:57.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, yes.

00:48:57.500 --> 00:48:58.550 align:middle line:90%
That's a good point.

00:48:58.550 --> 00:49:01.690 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Let that be your
guiding light is love,

00:49:01.690 --> 00:49:04.210 align:middle line:84%
and love in yourself,
love in other people.

00:49:04.210 --> 00:49:07.320 align:middle line:84%
And love feeds you
in all situations.

00:49:07.320 --> 00:49:08.370 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What about death?

00:49:08.370 --> 00:49:11.640 align:middle line:84%
What about
surrendering to death?

00:49:11.640 --> 00:49:13.790 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Well, it's inevitable.

00:49:13.790 --> 00:49:15.640 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's true.

00:49:15.640 --> 00:49:19.185 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: And as an
intuitive, I guess

00:49:19.185 --> 00:49:21.560 align:middle line:84%
I have an advantage in a way
where I've been able to tune

00:49:21.560 --> 00:49:25.640 align:middle line:84%
in to death and know that
it's nothing to fear.

00:49:25.640 --> 00:49:27.880 align:middle line:84%
And I've known that since
I've been a little girl.

00:49:27.880 --> 00:49:28.910 align:middle line:90%
So I've always--

00:49:28.910 --> 00:49:31.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What do you mean?

00:49:31.050 --> 00:49:33.520 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Our spirits
will become more radiant,

00:49:33.520 --> 00:49:36.350 align:middle line:84%
and you'll be more yourselves
in so many ways you can't even

00:49:36.350 --> 00:49:37.050 align:middle line:90%
envision it.

00:49:37.050 --> 00:49:39.260 align:middle line:84%
And we're so connected
to this body.

00:49:39.260 --> 00:49:40.760 align:middle line:84%
I love this package
I've been given.

00:49:40.760 --> 00:49:41.570 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

00:49:41.570 --> 00:49:43.200 align:middle line:84%
And I don't want to
give it up either,

00:49:43.200 --> 00:49:45.980 align:middle line:90%
but this is time limited.

00:49:45.980 --> 00:49:48.040 align:middle line:84%
So I'm going to enjoy
it while I have it.

00:49:48.040 --> 00:49:51.340 align:middle line:84%
But I once went to a medium
in the UK, and she said to me,

00:49:51.340 --> 00:49:54.700 align:middle line:84%
you have more friends on the
other side than you do here.

00:49:54.700 --> 00:49:55.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, interesting.

00:49:55.700 --> 00:49:56.340 align:middle line:90%
Interesting.

00:49:56.340 --> 00:49:58.450 align:middle line:84%
So you're excited
to get there, right?

00:49:58.450 --> 00:49:59.130 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: No.

00:49:59.130 --> 00:49:59.690 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, I
mean, not excited,

00:49:59.690 --> 00:50:01.320 align:middle line:84%
but when you get
there, it's not going

00:50:01.320 --> 00:50:06.190 align:middle line:84%
to be the end of-- it's not
going to be as devastating.

00:50:06.190 --> 00:50:08.410 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: It's not going
to be devastating at all.

00:50:08.410 --> 00:50:10.590 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's what's so
mind blowing about it.

00:50:10.590 --> 00:50:12.190 align:middle line:84%
It's not going to
be devastating.

00:50:12.190 --> 00:50:13.980 align:middle line:90%
It's not about devastation.

00:50:13.980 --> 00:50:17.090 align:middle line:84%
The loss that people go
through here when you go,

00:50:17.090 --> 00:50:20.310 align:middle line:84%
it will be devastating
for them to lose you.

00:50:20.310 --> 00:50:23.760 align:middle line:84%
But that's different than
you going to the other side.

00:50:23.760 --> 00:50:27.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: A friend of mine just
lost his mother to cancer,

00:50:27.270 --> 00:50:30.280 align:middle line:84%
but he had the privilege
of spending her last two

00:50:30.280 --> 00:50:32.740 align:middle line:90%
weeks of life with her.

00:50:32.740 --> 00:50:37.110 align:middle line:84%
And he sat by her bedside
for two solid weeks, day,

00:50:37.110 --> 00:50:38.340 align:middle line:90%
night, day, night.

00:50:38.340 --> 00:50:42.280 align:middle line:84%
And it turned into such a
beautiful experience for him

00:50:42.280 --> 00:50:44.960 align:middle line:90%
to watch his mother surrender.

00:50:44.960 --> 00:50:48.050 align:middle line:84%
And I know that that has got
to be such a challenging thing

00:50:48.050 --> 00:50:48.550 align:middle line:90%
to do.

00:50:48.550 --> 00:50:50.850 align:middle line:84%
And I was talking with
him during the process.

00:50:50.850 --> 00:50:56.170 align:middle line:84%
But he was so-- he looks
at her as such a hero

00:50:56.170 --> 00:50:59.310 align:middle line:84%
because she approached
death-- at the beginning,

00:50:59.310 --> 00:51:00.820 align:middle line:90%
it was extremely hard for her.

00:51:00.820 --> 00:51:03.660 align:middle line:84%
But then to eventually
surrender to the process

00:51:03.660 --> 00:51:07.070 align:middle line:84%
became a blissful
experience for both of them.

00:51:07.070 --> 00:51:09.120 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Oh, that's beautiful.

00:51:09.120 --> 00:51:11.620 align:middle line:84%
That's so, so beautiful to be
able to be with your parents

00:51:11.620 --> 00:51:13.290 align:middle line:90%
to help them surrender.

00:51:13.290 --> 00:51:16.580 align:middle line:84%
I also had that with both
my mother and my father,

00:51:16.580 --> 00:51:19.400 align:middle line:84%
and I helped them
surrender the physical body

00:51:19.400 --> 00:51:21.910 align:middle line:90%
and go to the other side.

00:51:21.910 --> 00:51:24.040 align:middle line:90%
And it's extremely powerful.

00:51:24.040 --> 00:51:26.820 align:middle line:84%
It's a letting go-- you
know, especially my mother,

00:51:26.820 --> 00:51:30.140 align:middle line:84%
the wrenching feeling of losing
the physical form of my mother.

00:51:30.140 --> 00:51:33.310 align:middle line:84%
I wrote about it
in "Second Sight."

00:51:33.310 --> 00:51:35.490 align:middle line:84%
It was very hard for me
at the time-- as a woman,

00:51:35.490 --> 00:51:37.370 align:middle line:84%
I was so connected
to my mother--

00:51:37.370 --> 00:51:40.120 align:middle line:90%
letting the physical form go.

00:51:40.120 --> 00:51:42.505 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you have a
relationship with her now?

00:51:42.505 --> 00:51:43.130 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: I do.

00:51:43.130 --> 00:51:46.800 align:middle line:84%
And my father actually is
closer to me than my mother.

00:51:46.800 --> 00:51:49.060 align:middle line:84%
My mother I think has
gone on to other things

00:51:49.060 --> 00:51:51.160 align:middle line:84%
more than my father
has made a commitment

00:51:51.160 --> 00:51:53.325 align:middle line:84%
to stay with me
until I pass over.

00:51:53.325 --> 00:51:53.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:51:53.960 --> 00:51:55.160 align:middle line:90%
Wonderful.

00:51:55.160 --> 00:51:58.080 align:middle line:84%
That experience
is-- when somebody's

00:51:58.080 --> 00:52:01.009 align:middle line:84%
taken from you suddenly,
it's a lot harder.

00:52:01.009 --> 00:52:02.300 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Oh, that's different.

00:52:02.300 --> 00:52:06.060 align:middle line:84%
That's much different because
you don't have time to prepare.

00:52:06.060 --> 00:52:09.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And it seems
unjust, especially a child.

00:52:09.510 --> 00:52:10.890 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Yes.

00:52:10.890 --> 00:52:12.330 align:middle line:90%
And life isn't fair.

00:52:12.330 --> 00:52:14.470 align:middle line:90%
It's not always about fairness.

00:52:14.470 --> 00:52:19.545 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Can you really
surrender to that kind of pain?

00:52:19.545 --> 00:52:23.130 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: You know, the heart is
stretched in so many ways that

00:52:23.130 --> 00:52:25.980 align:middle line:84%
cause us to surrender in so
many ways we think we can't.

00:52:25.980 --> 00:52:29.100 align:middle line:84%
And that aren't-- it's not fair
to ask us to surrender in those

00:52:29.100 --> 00:52:33.010 align:middle line:84%
ways, and yet we're
asked to do it.

00:52:33.010 --> 00:52:34.940 align:middle line:90%
We're faced with the impossible.

00:52:34.940 --> 00:52:36.020 align:middle line:90%
So you have a choice.

00:52:36.020 --> 00:52:39.810 align:middle line:84%
And you could either not
surrender and stay stuck in it,

00:52:39.810 --> 00:52:43.670 align:middle line:84%
or try, try, try to find
something larger to open up

00:52:43.670 --> 00:52:45.400 align:middle line:90%
to to carry you through.

00:52:45.400 --> 00:52:47.385 align:middle line:84%
Like what many mothers
do in that position,

00:52:47.385 --> 00:52:49.010 align:middle line:84%
in terms of their
surrender, is to help

00:52:49.010 --> 00:52:50.970 align:middle line:84%
other mothers who have
lost their children.

00:52:50.970 --> 00:52:55.430 align:middle line:84%
So they turn their grief
into helping others.

00:52:55.430 --> 00:52:57.296 align:middle line:90%
And that's no easy thing.

00:52:57.296 --> 00:52:58.170 align:middle line:90%
None of this is easy.

00:52:58.170 --> 00:53:00.150 align:middle line:84%
And surrenders
sometimes are-- you

00:53:00.150 --> 00:53:02.620 align:middle line:84%
don't know any way
you're going to do it.

00:53:02.620 --> 00:53:05.390 align:middle line:84%
And yet, that's
what's asked of you.

00:53:05.390 --> 00:53:08.480 align:middle line:84%
And so you either
do it or you don't.

00:53:08.480 --> 00:53:09.844 align:middle line:90%
And if you don't, you'll suffer.

00:53:09.844 --> 00:53:11.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I heard on
the news this morning

00:53:11.510 --> 00:53:14.130 align:middle line:90%
of a woman who lost her son.

00:53:14.130 --> 00:53:16.620 align:middle line:84%
And I think the
son's name was BJ.

00:53:16.620 --> 00:53:20.910 align:middle line:84%
And he-- she took
his ashes and gave it

00:53:20.910 --> 00:53:25.560 align:middle line:84%
to individual people that were
going to fulfill his dreams.

00:53:25.560 --> 00:53:28.680 align:middle line:84%
So he always had this dream,
I guess, to go to space.

00:53:28.680 --> 00:53:30.920 align:middle line:84%
And there was a
situation where--

00:53:30.920 --> 00:53:32.690 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how
it happened, but it

00:53:32.690 --> 00:53:36.510 align:middle line:84%
was on the news about a rocket
that took his ashes into space

00:53:36.510 --> 00:53:39.960 align:middle line:84%
and not release
them, but you know,

00:53:39.960 --> 00:53:43.690 align:middle line:84%
she was fulfilling or helping
him fulfill his dreams

00:53:43.690 --> 00:53:46.090 align:middle line:90%
through-- that was her process.

00:53:46.090 --> 00:53:47.930 align:middle line:90%
And it was an amazing story.

00:53:47.930 --> 00:53:49.650 align:middle line:84%
And there are so many
stories like that.

00:53:49.650 --> 00:53:50.930 align:middle line:90%
It's definitely a process.

00:53:50.930 --> 00:53:52.670 align:middle line:84%
There's no easy
answer for that one.

00:53:52.670 --> 00:53:54.750 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: There's no
easy answer except part

00:53:54.750 --> 00:53:57.150 align:middle line:84%
of understanding the
ecstasy of surrender

00:53:57.150 --> 00:53:59.660 align:middle line:84%
is knowing that our stay
here is time limited,

00:53:59.660 --> 00:54:01.820 align:middle line:84%
therefore we must
enjoy every moment.

00:54:01.820 --> 00:54:04.320 align:middle line:84%
And there will come a time
when everyone listening

00:54:04.320 --> 00:54:07.150 align:middle line:84%
to this show, including
us, will be gone.

00:54:07.150 --> 00:54:08.930 align:middle line:90%
And that's just how it is.

00:54:08.930 --> 00:54:12.810 align:middle line:84%
And you can fight it, or you
can try and flow with the fact

00:54:12.810 --> 00:54:15.570 align:middle line:84%
that your spirit is
real and powerful,

00:54:15.570 --> 00:54:17.190 align:middle line:90%
and it's not going anywhere.

00:54:17.190 --> 00:54:19.930 align:middle line:84%
And your body is temporary,
as much as your ego might

00:54:19.930 --> 00:54:24.435 align:middle line:84%
get so upset at that idea,
from an intuitive standpoint--

00:54:24.435 --> 00:54:26.310 align:middle line:84%
And that's why I'm asking
people to surrender

00:54:26.310 --> 00:54:27.690 align:middle line:90%
to their intuition.

00:54:27.690 --> 00:54:29.710 align:middle line:84%
From an intuitive
standpoint, you

00:54:29.710 --> 00:54:33.520 align:middle line:84%
can get a yes on
I'm going to be OK.

00:54:33.520 --> 00:54:35.300 align:middle line:84%
When you really go
deep in yourself,

00:54:35.300 --> 00:54:36.770 align:middle line:90%
and you tune in to it.

00:54:36.770 --> 00:54:38.410 align:middle line:84%
There's a meditation
in the book that I

00:54:38.410 --> 00:54:40.770 align:middle line:84%
suggest for everyone
going through this that's

00:54:40.770 --> 00:54:43.620 align:middle line:84%
questioning on
experiencing death.

00:54:43.620 --> 00:54:46.940 align:middle line:84%
And I take people
into the death space

00:54:46.940 --> 00:54:50.360 align:middle line:84%
and how to surrender to
that very slowly so you

00:54:50.360 --> 00:54:53.590 align:middle line:84%
can get an intuitive
sense of what it is.

00:54:53.590 --> 00:54:58.580 align:middle line:84%
And our society has made
such a big deal out of it.

00:54:58.580 --> 00:55:00.900 align:middle line:84%
And if you want to do the
meditation in the book,

00:55:00.900 --> 00:55:03.890 align:middle line:84%
you can do it slowly where you
picture death eight feet away,

00:55:03.890 --> 00:55:08.270 align:middle line:84%
seven feet away, six feet, then
slowly, then, merging with it

00:55:08.270 --> 00:55:09.890 align:middle line:84%
and feeling-- you're
not going to die.

00:55:09.890 --> 00:55:10.650 align:middle line:90%
Don't worry.

00:55:10.650 --> 00:55:13.890 align:middle line:84%
People always think they will,
but it doesn't work that way.

00:55:13.890 --> 00:55:15.276 align:middle line:90%
It's just an energy.

00:55:15.276 --> 00:55:16.650 align:middle line:84%
It's there from
the moment you're

00:55:16.650 --> 00:55:17.920 align:middle line:90%
born to the moment you die.

00:55:17.920 --> 00:55:21.220 align:middle line:84%
Death is a very creative
energy, so much so it helps you

00:55:21.220 --> 00:55:23.570 align:middle line:84%
with your transition
to the other side.

00:55:23.570 --> 00:55:25.660 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Interesting
to not be as painful.

00:55:25.660 --> 00:55:28.430 align:middle line:84%
There are certain cultures
that the minute you're born,

00:55:28.430 --> 00:55:30.690 align:middle line:90%
you start talking about death.

00:55:30.690 --> 00:55:33.480 align:middle line:84%
And it's part of
life, as part of life.

00:55:33.480 --> 00:55:36.540 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: We're death
phobic in this society.

00:55:36.540 --> 00:55:38.710 align:middle line:84%
But surrender-- that's
the final surrender.

00:55:38.710 --> 00:55:40.480 align:middle line:84%
But in the meantime,
we have lots

00:55:40.480 --> 00:55:43.980 align:middle line:84%
of years to practice
other forms of surrender

00:55:43.980 --> 00:55:47.030 align:middle line:84%
and feel the release, because
you want to feel the release.

00:55:47.030 --> 00:55:48.562 align:middle line:84%
And especially,
if you're going--

00:55:48.562 --> 00:55:51.520 align:middle line:84%
you're ending a relationship,
and you're going through grief,

00:55:51.520 --> 00:55:54.875 align:middle line:84%
you know, you have to
release the person,

00:55:54.875 --> 00:55:58.950 align:middle line:84%
you know, no matter how
heartbroken you are.

00:55:58.950 --> 00:56:00.170 align:middle line:90%
I love you.

00:56:00.170 --> 00:56:01.030 align:middle line:90%
I adore you.

00:56:01.030 --> 00:56:02.090 align:middle line:90%
It didn't work out.

00:56:02.090 --> 00:56:04.395 align:middle line:90%
I release you.

00:56:04.395 --> 00:56:07.480 align:middle line:84%
And then say that
mantra over and over

00:56:07.480 --> 00:56:11.450 align:middle line:84%
so that you can go
on with your life.

00:56:11.450 --> 00:56:14.950 align:middle line:84%
It's very important to surrender
to your future and your present

00:56:14.950 --> 00:56:17.660 align:middle line:84%
and not stay stuck in what
didn't work, no matter

00:56:17.660 --> 00:56:19.110 align:middle line:90%
how unfair that was.

00:56:19.110 --> 00:56:21.560 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Even in the
situation of a divorce?

00:56:21.560 --> 00:56:22.352 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Anything.

00:56:22.352 --> 00:56:23.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah, anything.

00:56:23.310 --> 00:56:24.390 align:middle line:90%
Very powerful advice.

00:56:24.390 --> 00:56:25.890 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Love is number one.

00:56:25.890 --> 00:56:28.650 align:middle line:84%
You move towards love
and towards the heart

00:56:28.650 --> 00:56:30.230 align:middle line:84%
no matter how much
you've been hurt.

00:56:30.230 --> 00:56:31.920 align:middle line:90%
And is that a big undertaking?

00:56:31.920 --> 00:56:35.710 align:middle line:84%
I'd say yes, but that's
what this is all about.

00:56:35.710 --> 00:56:39.000 align:middle line:84%
And you don't have to
do it, but if you really

00:56:39.000 --> 00:56:41.400 align:middle line:84%
want to expand and
feel the ecstasy,

00:56:41.400 --> 00:56:42.930 align:middle line:90%
this is a door into it.

00:56:42.930 --> 00:56:44.220 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: A good way to do it.

00:56:44.220 --> 00:56:47.110 align:middle line:84%
We're going to take a look at
a clip that-- a piece of video

00:56:47.110 --> 00:56:49.080 align:middle line:90%
that you interviewed Ram Dass.

00:56:49.080 --> 00:56:50.760 align:middle line:90%
And talk about surrendering.

00:56:50.760 --> 00:56:52.880 align:middle line:84%
Ram Dass had a stroke
several years ago.

00:56:52.880 --> 00:56:56.250 align:middle line:84%
And his-- the way that
he talks, there's long

00:56:56.250 --> 00:56:58.590 align:middle line:84%
pauses between the
times that he talks,

00:56:58.590 --> 00:57:01.580 align:middle line:84%
but they're so
filled with energy.

00:57:01.580 --> 00:57:02.250 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:57:02.250 --> 00:57:04.210 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:57:04.210 --> 00:57:15.995 align:middle line:84%
>>RAM DASS: In the
West-- in the West,

00:57:15.995 --> 00:57:19.710 align:middle line:84%
they shy away from
the word surrender

00:57:19.710 --> 00:57:23.950 align:middle line:84%
because it means you
surrender to somebody.

00:57:23.950 --> 00:57:27.205 align:middle line:90%


00:57:27.205 --> 00:57:34.700 align:middle line:84%
And when I say, I'm
surrendering to Maharaj Ji,

00:57:34.700 --> 00:57:37.614 align:middle line:90%
the Maharaj Ji is in my heart.

00:57:37.614 --> 00:57:44.350 align:middle line:90%


00:57:44.350 --> 00:57:55.020 align:middle line:84%
I'm surrendering to my
intuition, my wisdom.

00:57:55.020 --> 00:58:05.320 align:middle line:90%


00:58:05.320 --> 00:58:17.810 align:middle line:84%
Wisdom that I've gathered
subjectively, not objectively.

00:58:17.810 --> 00:58:19.310 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What was
that interview like

00:58:19.310 --> 00:58:22.970 align:middle line:84%
for you to sit with Ram Dass
and those beautiful pauses

00:58:22.970 --> 00:58:24.780 align:middle line:84%
that he has between
his teachings?

00:58:24.780 --> 00:58:27.666 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Yes, well actually,
he was interviewing me.

00:58:27.666 --> 00:58:28.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: He was?

00:58:28.290 --> 00:58:29.095 align:middle line:90%
Oh, my gosh.

00:58:29.095 --> 00:58:29.678 align:middle line:90%
>>ORLOFF: Yes.

00:58:29.678 --> 00:58:31.220 align:middle line:90%
I flew out to Maui to his home.

00:58:31.220 --> 00:58:35.025 align:middle line:84%
He invited me there to be part
of a webcast to his community.

00:58:35.025 --> 00:58:36.025 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, interesting.

00:58:36.025 --> 00:58:38.070 align:middle line:90%
How wonderful.

00:58:38.070 --> 00:58:41.770 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: So it was probably
my most favorite interview

00:58:41.770 --> 00:58:45.330 align:middle line:84%
in my entire life because
he gives off so much love,

00:58:45.330 --> 00:58:48.790 align:middle line:90%
and he's not that verbal.

00:58:48.790 --> 00:58:51.870 align:middle line:84%
So it was about nonverbally
communicating with him.

00:58:51.870 --> 00:58:54.270 align:middle line:84%
It's the opposite of
the soundbite culture.

00:58:54.270 --> 00:58:56.690 align:middle line:84%
It was flowing with
the love and the energy

00:58:56.690 --> 00:58:58.720 align:middle line:84%
and the brilliance
and his-- I kept

00:58:58.720 --> 00:59:01.190 align:middle line:84%
wanting to hug him
the whole time.

00:59:01.190 --> 00:59:03.630 align:middle line:90%
It's a beautiful interview.

00:59:03.630 --> 00:59:04.600 align:middle line:90%
I was so happy.

00:59:04.600 --> 00:59:06.830 align:middle line:84%
And we were looking out
onto the coast in Maui.

00:59:06.830 --> 00:59:09.830 align:middle line:84%
And we had a circle of
nice people around us

00:59:09.830 --> 00:59:10.780 align:middle line:90%
who were beaming love.

00:59:10.780 --> 00:59:13.082 align:middle line:84%
It was quite a wonderful
experience for me.

00:59:13.082 --> 00:59:14.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Talk about surrender.

00:59:14.290 --> 00:59:15.270 align:middle line:90%
Surrendering to love.

00:59:15.270 --> 00:59:15.940 align:middle line:90%
It's beautiful.

00:59:15.940 --> 00:59:19.110 align:middle line:84%
Well, thank you so much
for surrendering with me

00:59:19.110 --> 00:59:21.650 align:middle line:84%
and helping me learn
about surrender.

00:59:21.650 --> 00:59:23.720 align:middle line:90%
And I appreciate you being here.

00:59:23.720 --> 00:59:24.990 align:middle line:90%
Thank you so much, Judith.

00:59:24.990 --> 00:59:26.640 align:middle line:84%
>>ORLOFF: Oh, you're
so welcome, Lisa.

